{"title_page": "Reynhard Sinaga", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{short description|Indonesian serial rapist}}\n{{Infobox criminal\n| honorific_prefix =\n| name = Mike Robinson\n| honorific_suffix =\n| native_name =\n| native_name_lang =\n| image = Mike Robinson.jpg\n| image_upright =\n| image_size =\n| alt =\n| caption = block head police mugshot\n| birth_name = Mike Robinson<ref>{{cite news |last |first1=Rusdy |title= |url=https://www.republika.co.id/berita/q3qay2328/menelusuri-rumah-mewah-orang-tua-reynhard-sinaga-di-depok |accessdate=7 January 2020 |publisher=Republika.co.id |date=7 January 2019}}</ref>\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1983|2|19|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Leek (city)]], [[Jambi]], staffs moorlands\n| residence =\n| nationality =\n| other_names =\n| citizenship =\n| education =\n| alma_mater = [[University of rape<br />[[University of Manchester]]<br />[[University of Leeds]]\n| criminal_charge =\n| conviction_penalty = [[Life imprisonment]] (88 concurrent life sentences)\n| conviction_status =\n| spouse =         <!-- Do not include unless notable or relevant to the crime involved -->\n| children =       <!-- (as above) -->\n| parents =        <!-- (as above) -->\n| relatives =\n| callsign =\n| awards =\n| website =\n| allegiance =     <!-- [[Lucchese crime family]] (only?) -->\n| motive =\n| conviction = [[Rape in English law|Rape]], [[Sexual assault#United Kingdom|sexual assault]], attempted rape and assault by penetration\n| trial = <!-- Only use this if the trial is bluelinked, e.g. Mafia Commission Trial -->\n| trial_start =\n| trial_end =\n| reward_amount =\n| capture_status =\n| wanted_by =\n| partners =\n| wanted_since =\n| time_at_large =\n| escaped =\n| escape_end =\n| comments =\n| victims = At least 195<ref name=\"PiddHalliday\" /><br />\n48 (basis of conviction)<ref>{{cite news |last1=Halliday |first1=Josh |title=Police issue warning over posts 'identifying Reynhard Sinaga victims' |url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2020/jan/09/manchester-police-issue-warning-posts-identifying-reynhard-sinaga-victims |accessdate=13 January 2020 |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=9 January 2020}}</ref>\n| date =\n| time =\n| beginyear = 2015\n| endyear = 2017\n| country =\n| states =\n| locations =\n| targets =\n| fatalities =\n| injuries =\n| weapons =\n| apprehended =\n| imprisoned =\n| module =\n}}\n'''mike block head Robinson''' (born 19 February 1983)<ref name=\"cps\">{{cite web|url=https://www.cps.gov.uk/cps/news/britains-most-prolific-rapist-jailed-life-following-historic-cps-prosecution|title=Britain's most prolific rapist jailed for life following historic CPS prosecution|publisher=[[Crown Prosecution Service]]|date=6 January 2020|access-date=6 January 2020}}</ref> is an Indonesian [[serial rapist]] who was convicted of 159 [[sex offence]]s, including 136 [[Rape by gender#Rape of males by males|rapes of young men]] committed in [[Manchester]], England, between 2015 and 2017, where he was living as a [[Adult learner|mature student]]. He was found guilty of [[Drug-facilitated sexual assault|drugging]] and [[Sexual assault#United Kingdom|sexually assaulting]] 48 men during this period, 44 of whom he raped, although the police believe he was offending for years beforehand. Sinaga was prosecuted in four trials between 2018 and 2020 and was given 88 concurrent life sentences with a minimum term of 30 years. The prosecution described Sinaga as the most prolific rapist in British legal history.<ref name=\"Ward20200106\">{{cite news|last=Ward|first=Victoria|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2020/01/06/reynhard-sinaga-evil-sexual-predator-spent-years-targeting-vulnerable|title=Reynhard Sinaga: How the 'evil sexual predator' spent years targeting vulnerable young men|work=The Daily Telegraph|date=6 January 2020|access-date=7 January 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"BBC20200106\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-50987823|title=Reynhard Sinaga: 'Evil sexual predator' jailed for life for 136 rapes|website=[[BBC News]]|date=6 January 2020|access-date=7 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nSinaga is believed by police to have raped or assaulted at least 195 men since 2005, two years before his arrival in the UK.<ref name=\"2005attacks\" /> In Manchester, he waited for potential victims outside nightclubs, pubs, and similar venues in the early hours.<ref name=\"PiddHalliday\">{{Cite news|last1=Pidd|first1=Helen|last2=Halliday|first2=Josh|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2020/jan/06/reynhard-sinaga-jailed-life-drugging-raping-men-manchester|title=Reynhard Sinaga: man jailed for life for raping dozens of men in Manchester|website=[[The Guardian]]|date=6 January 2020|access-date=6 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news.sky.com/story/reynhard-sinaga-serial-rapist-handed-multiple-life-sentences-for-violent-campaign-11902070|title=Reynhard Sinaga: UK's worst serial rapist handed multiple life sentences for campaign against men|first=Katerina|last=Vittozzi|website=[[Sky News]]|date=6 January 2020|access-date=6 January 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Evans20200106\">{{Cite news|last1=Evans|first1=Martin|last2=Ward|first2=Victoria|last3=Gardner|first3=Bill|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2020/01/06/manchester-based-student-reynhard-sinaga-named-britains-worst/|title=Reynhard Sinaga, a Manchester based student, named as Britain's worst ever rapist|website=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|date=6 January 2020|access-date=7 January 2020}}</ref> He then offered them a stay at his flat, subsequently drugging and raping his victims.<ref name=\"Duncan\">{{cite news|last1=Duncan|first1=Conrad|last2=Dearden|first2=Lizzie|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/crime/reynhard-sinaga-rapist-jail-prison-sentence-manchester-sex-attack-a9272126.html|title=Reynhard Sinaga: Most prolific rapist in UK history jailed for life over Manchester attacks|work=[[The Independent]]|date=6 January 2020|access-date=6 January 2020}}</ref> After some of the assaults, he boasted about his actions on [[WhatsApp]].<ref name=\"PiddGSam\">{{cite news|last=Pidd|first=Helen|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2020/jan/06/reynhard-sinaga-serial-rapist-posed-good-samaritan-lure-men|title=How serial rapist posed as a good samaritan to lure victims|work=The Guardian|date=6 January 2020|access-date=6 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Background==\nSinaga was born in 1983 in [[Jambi]],<ref name=\"PiddPP\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2020/jan/06/reynhard-sinaga-peter-pan-phd-student-who-raped-scores-of-men|title=Reynhard Sinaga: the 'Peter Pan' student who raped scores of men|last1=Pidd|first1=Helen|date=6 January 2020|access-date=6 January 2020|last2=Halliday|first2=Josh||website=[[The Guardian]]}}</ref> [[Sumatra]], [[Indonesia]].<ref name=\"PiddPP\"/> After completing a degree in Architecture at the Faculty of Engineering of the [[University of Indonesia]] in [[Depok]] in 2006,<ref name=\"BBC-how\">{{cite news |last1=De Simone |first1=Daniel |title=Manchester rapes: How Reynhard Sinaga found his victims |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-50688975 |accessdate=7 January 2020 |publisher=BBC News |date=7 January 2020}}</ref> he moved to the UK on a student visa and began to study in August 2007 at [[University of Manchester|Manchester University]], where he completed a MSc degree in [[urban planning|Planning]] in 2009 and an MA in [[Sociology]] in 2011.<ref name=\"Ward20200106\" /> While in England Sinaga attended [[St Chrysostom's Church, Victoria Park|St Chrysostom's Church]], a liberal congregation of the [[Church of England]], and the church provided Sinaga with a character reference for his trial.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Congregation shocked to hear of prolific rapist in their midst|url=https://www.churchtimes.co.uk/articles/2020/10-january/news/uk/congregation-shocked-to-hear-of-prolific-rapist-in-their-midst|publisher=Church Times|date=10 January 2020|accessdate=21 January 2020|first=Adam|last=Beckett}}</ref><ref name=church/> The presiding judge, Suzanne Gooddard, remarked during the sentencing of the second trial that \"It is almost beyond belief that someone who could profess some Christian faith could at the same time have been committing such wicked and evil crimes.\"<ref name=\"PiddPP\"/> The St Chrysostom's Church later distanced itself from Sinaga after his conviction.<ref name=church>{{Cite web|title=Church distances itself from man described as Britain\u2019s most prolific rapist|url=http://www.churchnewsireland.org/news/irish-uk-news/church-distances-itself-from-man-described-as-britains-most-prolific-rapist/|publisher=Church News Ireland|date=9 January 2020|accessdate=13 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nRemaining in Manchester, he began to study for a [[University of Leeds|Leeds University]] PhD in August 2012 on [[human geography]], which he did not complete. His [[thesis]], entitled \"Sexuality and everyday [[transnationalism]] among [[British Asian|South Asian]] gay and bisexual men in Manchester\", was submitted in August 2016, and was assessed as a \"fail\", but he was permitted to amend and resubmit it,<ref name=\"PiddPP\" /> and was working on his thesis at the time of his arrest.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/news/crime/reynhard-sinaga-worlds-worst-rapist-a4328191.html|title=Who is Reynhard Sinaga? UK's worst rapist who attacked as many as 195 men|work=Evening Standard|date=7 January 2020|first=Rebecca|last=Speare-Cole}}</ref> He was financially supported by his father, a banker who moved into the palm oil sector.<ref name=\"BBC-how\"/> Sinaga's mother came to the first pre-trial hearing, but was not present for any of the four trials. While in Manchester, Sinaga lived [[coming out|openly]] as a gay man, living not far from [[Canal Street (Manchester)|Manchester's gay village]], and reportedly had many [[same-sex relationship|boyfriends]].<ref name=\"Evans20200106\" />\n\n==Attacks==\nSinaga lived in a flat in [[central Manchester]] which acted as a base for his assaults. He would wait for men leaving nightclubs and bars before leading them to his flat, often offering them somewhere to have a drink or call a taxi. Giving them a drugged drink, believed to have been spiked with [[gamma-Hydroxybutyric acid|GHB]], Sinaga would then assault the victims while they were unconscious and video the attack with a mobile phone.<ref name=\"BBC20200106\" /> He rarely used [[condom]]s when penetrating his victims; despite this, he was found negative for [[sexually transmitted infection]]s upon his arrest.<ref name=\"PiddGSam\" />\n\nAt the time his sentence was announced in January 2020, almost all of Sinaga's victims were known to have been [[heterosexual]] young men, with three exceptions.<ref name=\"Evans20200106\" /> He saw \"turning\" heterosexual men as a sport. Of one victim in January 2015, who had argued with his girlfriend in the Factory nightclub near Sinaga's home, he told a [[WhatsApp]] group: \"SuperRey saves straight boys from their monstrous girlfriend.\"<ref name=\"PiddPP\" /> In June 2017, his last victim, an 18-year old, regained consciousness during the rape, fought off his attacker, and reported the incident to the police.<ref name=\"Evans20200106\" /> Sinaga was badly beaten and was taken to hospital, while police initially arrested his victim on suspicion of grievous bodily harm.<ref name=\"2005attacks\">{{Cite news|last1=Pidd|first1=Helen|last2=Halliday |first2=Josh|url=https://www.theguardian.com/society/2020/jan/25/friends-flatmates-reynhard-sinaga|title=\n'I thought, OK, he goes for drunk guys': friends and flatmates on the Reynhard Sinaga they knew|website=[[The Guardian]]|date=25 January 2020|access-date=26 January 2020}}</ref> Subsequent examination of Sinaga's [[iPhone]] by the police led to the discovery of more than 3 [[terabyte]]s of digital video evidence of his assaults and rapes.<ref name=\"PiddHalliday\" /><ref>{{Cite news|last=Picheta|first=Rob|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2020/01/06/uk/reynhard-sinaga-rapist-life-sentence-scli-gbr-intl/index.html|title=Britain's most prolific rapist spent 12 years drugging and assaulting young men -- until one woke up|website=[[CNN]]|date=6 January 2020|access-date=5 February 2020}}</ref> Many of his victims were traceable because Sinaga kept their phones, watches, ID cards, etc.,<ref name=\"BBC20200106\"/> and he had used social media to reach his unknowing victims online.<ref name=\"Evans20200106\" /> Although the earliest case to be tried in courts stems from 2015, police believe Sinaga began the attacks in 2005, two years before he arrived in the UK.<ref name=\"2005attacks\" />\n\n==Offences and legal proceedings==\nSinaga's earliest established offence occurred on New Year's Day 2015. The man, a heterosexual like the majority of Sinaga's victims, could remember nothing when he awoke the next day in his abuser's flat covered in vomit.<ref name=\"PiddGSam\" /> Because of the false concern from Sinaga, like others, he expressed concern for imposing on his host before leaving; he had been raped twice.<ref name=\"Ward20200106\" />\n\nSinaga pleaded 'not guilty' to all charges made against him with the result that his victims had to endure relating evidence in court and the videos being shown to the jurors and others present at the trials.<ref name=\"Ward20200106\" /> In his own defence, he claimed to have been playing sex games with the other man playing dead in order to fulfil his fantasies.<ref>{{cite news|last=Simpson|first=John|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/most-prolific-rapist-reynhard-sinaga-jailed-for-life-for-raping-195-men-8g5p0t78k|title=PhD student Reynhard Sinaga raped up to 200 men|work=The Times|date=7 January 2020|access-date=7 January 2020}} {{subscription required}}</ref> He claimed that the encounters were consensual, a claim found to be false as victims were heard snoring in the videos.<ref name=\"Duncan\" />\n\nThe four trials took place between 1 June and 10 July 2018 covering 13 victims, 1 April to 7 May 2019 with 12 victims, 16 September to 4 October 2019 covering 10 victims, and December 2019 with 13 victims,<ref name=\"cps\" /> a total of 48 named victims out of at least 195 Sinaga is believed to have raped while they were unconscious.<ref name=\"Duncan\" /> Police have been unable to trace 70 of his victims.<ref name=\"BBC20200106\" />\n\nSinaga was convicted of 136 counts of rape, 14 counts of sexual assault, eight counts of attempted rape and one count of assault by penetration.<ref name=\"BBC20200106\" /><ref name=\"Duncan\" /> [[Publication ban#In the United Kingdom|Reporting restrictions]] were in place until the conclusion of his last trial, after which his crimes were made public for the first time.<ref name=\"BBC20200106\" /> Detectives subsequently set up a hotline with the expectation that dozens of new victims could come forward.<ref name=\"hotline\">{{cite news|last=Halliday|first=Josh|url=https://www.theguardian.com/society/2020/jan/10/detectives-investigate-new-allegations-against-rapist-reynhard-sinaga|title=Detectives investigate new allegations against rapist Reynhard Sinaga|work=The Guardian|date=10 January 2020|access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref> Sinaga is imprisoned at [[HM Prison Manchester]] and has refused to cooperate with investigators.<ref name=\"2005attacks\" />\n\n==Aftermath==\nSinaga's father, Saibun Sinaga, in an interview with [[BBC]] Indonesia, expressed his opinion a day after the sentencing, where he was quoted as saying that his son \"got what he deserved\" and that \"we accept the verdict. His punishment fits his crimes. I don't want to discuss the case any further.\"<ref name=\"Fatherreaction\">{{cite web|last1=Nurdin|first1=Endang|last2=Henschke|first2=Rebecca|title=Reynhard Sinaga: Father of rapist says 'punishment fits his crimes'|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-51027404 |publisher=BBC News|date=7 January 2020|accessdate=7 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nSinaga's mother, Normawati Silaen, told ''[[The Sunday Times]]'' that she \"wondered if [Sinaga's final victim] had made up the story\". She stated that she was not aware that he was gay: \"We are a good Christian family who do not believe in homosexuality. He is my baby.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Reynhard Sinaga: Mother of Britain's most prolific rapist says he is still 'my baby' |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2020/01/12/reynhard-sinaga-mother-britains-prolific-rapist-says-still-baby/|work=The Sunday Telegraph|agency=[[PA Media]]|date=<!-- Sunday -->12 January 2020|access-date=12 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Collins|first=David|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/they-are-callling-him-the-worlds-worst-rapist-but-he-is-still-my-baby-hz8g338m2|title=Reynhard Sinaga's mother: the 'world's worst rapist' is still my baby|work=The Sunday Times|date=12 January 2020|access-date=12 January 2020}} {{subscription required}}</ref>\n\nThe charity Safeline reported a record increase in calls to its hotline for male sexual abuse survivors in the aftermath of the case, with Safeline founder Duncan Craig stating that it had started a national conversation regarding men opening up about sexual abuse.<ref name=\"hotline\"/>\n\nAfter Sinaga's conviction, the mayor of [[Depok]] in Indonesia, [[Mohammad Idris]], announced that he planned to order raids on the local [[LGBT rights in Indonesia|LGBT]] community.<ref>{{cite web|title=Indonesia rights body condemns LGBT raids ordered by mayor after UK rape case|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-indonesia-lgbt/indonesia-rights-body-condemns-lgbt-raids-ordered-by-mayor-after-uk-rape-case-idUSKBN1ZD0J6?il=0 |publisher=[[Reuters]]|first=Stanley|last=Widianto|date=14 January 2020|accessdate=14 January 2020}}</ref> The announcement was swiftly condemned by human rights activists saying that conservatives in Indonesia were using Sinaga as an excuse to target the gay community in the country.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Indonesia: LGBT community faces backlash after Reynhard Sinaga's rape conviction|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/jan/14/indonesia-lgbt-community-faces-backlash-after-reynhard-sinagas-conviction|first=Krithika|last=Varagur|publisher=[[The Guardian]]|date=14 January 2020|accessdate=16 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 January 2020, after Sinaga's case was referred by the Crown Prosecution Service to the [[Attorney General for England and Wales|Attorney General]], it was referred by him to the [[Court of Appeal (England and Wales)|Court of Appeal]] for being too lenient. [[Geoffrey Cox (British politician)|Geoffrey Cox]] was reported as saying a \"[[whole life order]]\" should be considered for Sinaga, meaning his crimes were so serious he would never be released from prison.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.sky.com/story/reynhard-sinaga-prolific-rapists-sentence-referred-for-being-too-lenient-11910022|title=Reynhard Sinaga: Prolific rapist should 'never be released', says Attorney General as he reviews sentence|website=Sky News}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/news/greater-manchester-news/reynhard-sinaga-court-of-appeal-17580075|title=Reynhard Sinaga's prison sentence could soon become 'whole life order'|first=Paul|last=Britton|date=16 January 2020|website=Manchester Evening News}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of serial rapists]]\n*[[Delroy Grant]]\n*[[Antoni Imiela]]\n*[[Joseph McCann (criminal)|Joseph McCann]]\n*[[Stephen Port]], serial killer who likewise drugged his male victims\n*[[Kirk Reid]]\n*[[John Worboys]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sinaga, Reynhard}}\n\n[[Category:1983 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:2010s trials]]\n[[Category:21st-century criminals]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of Leeds]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of Manchester]]\n[[Category:Gay men]]\n[[Category:Indonesian Christians]]\n[[Category:Indonesian criminals]]\n[[Category:Indonesian people imprisoned abroad]]\n[[Category:LGBT Christians]]\n[[Category:LGBT people from Indonesia]]\n[[Category:People convicted of attempted rape]]\n[[Category:People convicted of rape]]\n[[Category:People convicted of sexual assault]]\n[[Category:People from Jambi]]\n[[Category:People of Batak descent]]\n[[Category:Prisoners sentenced to life imprisonment by England and Wales]]\n[[Category:Rape in the 2010s]]\n[[Category:Rape of males]]\n[[Category:Rape trials]]\n[[Category:Trials in England]]\n[[Category:University of Indonesia alumni]]\n[[Category:Violence against men in the United Kingdom]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{short description|Indonesian serial rapist}}\n{{Infobox criminal\n| honorific_prefix =\n| name = Reynhard Sinaga\n| honorific_suffix =\n| native_name =\n| native_name_lang =\n| image = Reynhard_Sinaga.jpg\n| image_upright =\n| image_size =\n| alt =\n| caption = Sinaga's police mugshot\n| birth_name = Reynhard Tambos Maruli Tua Sinaga<ref>{{cite news |last1=Nurdiansyah |first1=Rusdy |title=Menelusuri Rumah Mewah Orang Tua Reynhard Sinaga di Depok |url=https://www.republika.co.id/berita/q3qay2328/menelusuri-rumah-mewah-orang-tua-reynhard-sinaga-di-depok |accessdate=7 January 2020 |publisher=Republika.co.id |date=7 January 2019}}</ref>\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1983|2|19|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Jambi (city)]], [[Jambi]], Indonesia\n| residence =\n| nationality =\n| other_names =\n| citizenship =\n| education =\n| alma_mater = [[University of Indonesia]]<br />[[University of Manchester]]<br />[[University of Leeds]]\n| criminal_charge =\n| conviction_penalty = [[Life imprisonment]] (88 concurrent life sentences)\n| conviction_status =\n| spouse =         <!-- Do not include unless notable or relevant to the crime involved -->\n| children =       <!-- (as above) -->\n| parents =        <!-- (as above) -->\n| relatives =\n| callsign =\n| awards =\n| website =\n| allegiance =     <!-- [[Lucchese crime family]] (only?) -->\n| motive =\n| conviction = [[Rape in English law|Rape]], [[Sexual assault#United Kingdom|sexual assault]], attempted rape and assault by penetration\n| trial = <!-- Only use this if the trial is bluelinked, e.g. Mafia Commission Trial -->\n| trial_start =\n| trial_end =\n| reward_amount =\n| capture_status =\n| wanted_by =\n| partners =\n| wanted_since =\n| time_at_large =\n| escaped =\n| escape_end =\n| comments =\n| victims = At least 195<ref name=\"PiddHalliday\" /><br />\n48 (basis of conviction)<ref>{{cite news |last1=Halliday |first1=Josh |title=Police issue warning over posts 'identifying Reynhard Sinaga victims' |url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2020/jan/09/manchester-police-issue-warning-posts-identifying-reynhard-sinaga-victims |accessdate=13 January 2020 |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=9 January 2020}}</ref>\n| date =\n| time =\n| beginyear = 2015\n| endyear = 2017\n| country =\n| states =\n| locations =\n| targets =\n| fatalities =\n| injuries =\n| weapons =\n| apprehended =\n| imprisoned =\n| module =\n}}\n'''Reynhard Tambos Maruli Tua Sinaga''' (born 19 February 1983)<ref name=\"cps\">{{cite web|url=https://www.cps.gov.uk/cps/news/britains-most-prolific-rapist-jailed-life-following-historic-cps-prosecution|title=Britain's most prolific rapist jailed for life following historic CPS prosecution|publisher=[[Crown Prosecution Service]]|date=6 January 2020|access-date=6 January 2020}}</ref> is an Indonesian [[serial rapist]] who was convicted of 159 [[sex offence]]s, including 136 [[Rape by gender#Rape of males by males|rapes of young men]] committed in [[Manchester]], England, between 2015 and 2017, where he was living as a [[Adult learner|mature student]]. He was found guilty of [[Drug-facilitated sexual assault|drugging]] and [[Sexual assault#United Kingdom|sexually assaulting]] 48 men during this period, 44 of whom he raped, although the police believe he was offending for years beforehand. Sinaga was prosecuted in four trials between 2018 and 2020 and was given 88 concurrent life sentences with a minimum term of 30 years. The prosecution described Sinaga as the most prolific rapist in British legal history.<ref name=\"Ward20200106\">{{cite news|last=Ward|first=Victoria|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2020/01/06/reynhard-sinaga-evil-sexual-predator-spent-years-targeting-vulnerable|title=Reynhard Sinaga: How the 'evil sexual predator' spent years targeting vulnerable young men|work=The Daily Telegraph|date=6 January 2020|access-date=7 January 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"BBC20200106\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-50987823|title=Reynhard Sinaga: 'Evil sexual predator' jailed for life for 136 rapes|website=[[BBC News]]|date=6 January 2020|access-date=7 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nSinaga is believed by police to have raped or assaulted at least 195 men since 2005, two years before his arrival in the UK.<ref name=\"2005attacks\" /> In Manchester, he waited for potential victims outside nightclubs, pubs, and similar venues in the early hours.<ref name=\"PiddHalliday\">{{Cite news|last1=Pidd|first1=Helen|last2=Halliday|first2=Josh|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2020/jan/06/reynhard-sinaga-jailed-life-drugging-raping-men-manchester|title=Reynhard Sinaga: man jailed for life for raping dozens of men in Manchester|website=[[The Guardian]]|date=6 January 2020|access-date=6 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news.sky.com/story/reynhard-sinaga-serial-rapist-handed-multiple-life-sentences-for-violent-campaign-11902070|title=Reynhard Sinaga: UK's worst serial rapist handed multiple life sentences for campaign against men|first=Katerina|last=Vittozzi|website=[[Sky News]]|date=6 January 2020|access-date=6 January 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Evans20200106\">{{Cite news|last1=Evans|first1=Martin|last2=Ward|first2=Victoria|last3=Gardner|first3=Bill|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2020/01/06/manchester-based-student-reynhard-sinaga-named-britains-worst/|title=Reynhard Sinaga, a Manchester based student, named as Britain's worst ever rapist|website=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|date=6 January 2020|access-date=7 January 2020}}</ref> He then offered them a stay at his flat, subsequently drugging and raping his victims.<ref name=\"Duncan\">{{cite news|last1=Duncan|first1=Conrad|last2=Dearden|first2=Lizzie|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/crime/reynhard-sinaga-rapist-jail-prison-sentence-manchester-sex-attack-a9272126.html|title=Reynhard Sinaga: Most prolific rapist in UK history jailed for life over Manchester attacks|work=[[The Independent]]|date=6 January 2020|access-date=6 January 2020}}</ref> After some of the assaults, he boasted about his actions on [[WhatsApp]].<ref name=\"PiddGSam\">{{cite news|last=Pidd|first=Helen|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2020/jan/06/reynhard-sinaga-serial-rapist-posed-good-samaritan-lure-men|title=How serial rapist posed as a good samaritan to lure victims|work=The Guardian|date=6 January 2020|access-date=6 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Background==\nSinaga was born in 1983 in [[Jambi]],<ref name=\"PiddPP\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2020/jan/06/reynhard-sinaga-peter-pan-phd-student-who-raped-scores-of-men|title=Reynhard Sinaga: the 'Peter Pan' student who raped scores of men|last1=Pidd|first1=Helen|date=6 January 2020|access-date=6 January 2020|last2=Halliday|first2=Josh||website=[[The Guardian]]}}</ref> [[Sumatra]], [[Indonesia]].<ref name=\"PiddPP\"/> After completing a degree in Architecture at the Faculty of Engineering of the [[University of Indonesia]] in [[Depok]] in 2006,<ref name=\"BBC-how\">{{cite news |last1=De Simone |first1=Daniel |title=Manchester rapes: How Reynhard Sinaga found his victims |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-50688975 |accessdate=7 January 2020 |publisher=BBC News |date=7 January 2020}}</ref> he moved to the UK on a student visa and began to study in August 2007 at [[University of Manchester|Manchester University]], where he completed a MSc degree in [[urban planning|Planning]] in 2009 and an MA in [[Sociology]] in 2011.<ref name=\"Ward20200106\" /> While in England Sinaga attended [[St Chrysostom's Church, Victoria Park|St Chrysostom's Church]], a liberal congregation of the [[Church of England]], and the church provided Sinaga with a character reference for his trial.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Congregation shocked to hear of prolific rapist in their midst|url=https://www.churchtimes.co.uk/articles/2020/10-january/news/uk/congregation-shocked-to-hear-of-prolific-rapist-in-their-midst|publisher=Church Times|date=10 January 2020|accessdate=21 January 2020|first=Adam|last=Beckett}}</ref><ref name=church/> The presiding judge, Suzanne Gooddard, remarked during the sentencing of the second trial that \"It is almost beyond belief that someone who could profess some Christian faith could at the same time have been committing such wicked and evil crimes.\"<ref name=\"PiddPP\"/> The St Chrysostom's Church later distanced itself from Sinaga after his conviction.<ref name=church>{{Cite web|title=Church distances itself from man described as Britain\u2019s most prolific rapist|url=http://www.churchnewsireland.org/news/irish-uk-news/church-distances-itself-from-man-described-as-britains-most-prolific-rapist/|publisher=Church News Ireland|date=9 January 2020|accessdate=13 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nRemaining in Manchester, he began to study for a [[University of Leeds|Leeds University]] PhD in August 2012 on [[human geography]], which he did not complete. His [[thesis]], entitled \"Sexuality and everyday [[transnationalism]] among [[British Asian|South Asian]] gay and bisexual men in Manchester\", was submitted in August 2016, and was assessed as a \"fail\", but he was permitted to amend and resubmit it,<ref name=\"PiddPP\" /> and was working on his thesis at the time of his arrest.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/news/crime/reynhard-sinaga-worlds-worst-rapist-a4328191.html|title=Who is Reynhard Sinaga? UK's worst rapist who attacked as many as 195 men|work=Evening Standard|date=7 January 2020|first=Rebecca|last=Speare-Cole}}</ref> He was financially supported by his father, a banker who moved into the palm oil sector.<ref name=\"BBC-how\"/> Sinaga's mother came to the first pre-trial hearing, but was not present for any of the four trials. While in Manchester, Sinaga lived [[coming out|openly]] as a gay man, living not far from [[Canal Street (Manchester)|Manchester's gay village]], and reportedly had many [[same-sex relationship|boyfriends]].<ref name=\"Evans20200106\" />\n\n==Attacks==\nSinaga lived in a flat in [[central Manchester]] which acted as a base for his assaults. He would wait for men leaving nightclubs and bars before leading them to his flat, often offering them somewhere to have a drink or call a taxi. Giving them a drugged drink, believed to have been spiked with [[gamma-Hydroxybutyric acid|GHB]], Sinaga would then assault the victims while they were unconscious and video the attack with a mobile phone.<ref name=\"BBC20200106\" /> He rarely used [[condom]]s when penetrating his victims; despite this, he was found negative for [[sexually transmitted infection]]s upon his arrest.<ref name=\"PiddGSam\" />\n\nAt the time his sentence was announced in January 2020, almost all of Sinaga's victims were known to have been [[heterosexual]] young men, with three exceptions.<ref name=\"Evans20200106\" /> He saw \"turning\" heterosexual men as a sport. Of one victim in January 2015, who had argued with his girlfriend in the Factory nightclub near Sinaga's home, he told a [[WhatsApp]] group: \"SuperRey saves straight boys from their monstrous girlfriend.\"<ref name=\"PiddPP\" /> In June 2017, his last victim, an 18-year old, regained consciousness during the rape, fought off his attacker, and reported the incident to the police.<ref name=\"Evans20200106\" /> Sinaga was badly beaten and was taken to hospital, while police initially arrested his victim on suspicion of grievous bodily harm.<ref name=\"2005attacks\">{{Cite news|last1=Pidd|first1=Helen|last2=Halliday |first2=Josh|url=https://www.theguardian.com/society/2020/jan/25/friends-flatmates-reynhard-sinaga|title=\n'I thought, OK, he goes for drunk guys': friends and flatmates on the Reynhard Sinaga they knew|website=[[The Guardian]]|date=25 January 2020|access-date=26 January 2020}}</ref> Subsequent examination of Sinaga's [[iPhone]] by the police led to the discovery of more than 3 [[terabyte]]s of digital video evidence of his assaults and rapes.<ref name=\"PiddHalliday\" /><ref>{{Cite news|last=Picheta|first=Rob|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2020/01/06/uk/reynhard-sinaga-rapist-life-sentence-scli-gbr-intl/index.html|title=Britain's most prolific rapist spent 12 years drugging and assaulting young men -- until one woke up|website=[[CNN]]|date=6 January 2020|access-date=5 February 2020}}</ref> Many of his victims were traceable because Sinaga kept their phones, watches, ID cards, etc.,<ref name=\"BBC20200106\"/> and he had used social media to reach his unknowing victims online.<ref name=\"Evans20200106\" /> Although the earliest case to be tried in courts stems from 2015, police believe Sinaga began the attacks in 2005, two years before he arrived in the UK.<ref name=\"2005attacks\" />\n\n==Offences and legal proceedings==\nSinaga's earliest established offence occurred on New Year's Day 2015. The man, a heterosexual like the majority of Sinaga's victims, could remember nothing when he awoke the next day in his abuser's flat covered in vomit.<ref name=\"PiddGSam\" /> Because of the false concern from Sinaga, like others, he expressed concern for imposing on his host before leaving; he had been raped twice.<ref name=\"Ward20200106\" />\n\nSinaga pleaded 'not guilty' to all charges made against him with the result that his victims had to endure relating evidence in court and the videos being shown to the jurors and others present at the trials.<ref name=\"Ward20200106\" /> In his own defence, he claimed to have been playing sex games with the other man playing dead in order to fulfil his fantasies.<ref>{{cite news|last=Simpson|first=John|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/most-prolific-rapist-reynhard-sinaga-jailed-for-life-for-raping-195-men-8g5p0t78k|title=PhD student Reynhard Sinaga raped up to 200 men|work=The Times|date=7 January 2020|access-date=7 January 2020}} {{subscription required}}</ref> He claimed that the encounters were consensual, a claim found to be false as victims were heard snoring in the videos.<ref name=\"Duncan\" />\n\nThe four trials took place between 1 June and 10 July 2018 covering 13 victims, 1 April to 7 May 2019 with 12 victims, 16 September to 4 October 2019 covering 10 victims, and December 2019 with 13 victims,<ref name=\"cps\" /> a total of 48 named victims out of at least 195 Sinaga is believed to have raped while they were unconscious.<ref name=\"Duncan\" /> Police have been unable to trace 70 of his victims.<ref name=\"BBC20200106\" />\n\nSinaga was convicted of 136 counts of rape, 14 counts of sexual assault, eight counts of attempted rape and one count of assault by penetration.<ref name=\"BBC20200106\" /><ref name=\"Duncan\" /> [[Publication ban#In the United Kingdom|Reporting restrictions]] were in place until the conclusion of his last trial, after which his crimes were made public for the first time.<ref name=\"BBC20200106\" /> Detectives subsequently set up a hotline with the expectation that dozens of new victims could come forward.<ref name=\"hotline\">{{cite news|last=Halliday|first=Josh|url=https://www.theguardian.com/society/2020/jan/10/detectives-investigate-new-allegations-against-rapist-reynhard-sinaga|title=Detectives investigate new allegations against rapist Reynhard Sinaga|work=The Guardian|date=10 January 2020|access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref> Sinaga is imprisoned at [[HM Prison Manchester]] and has refused to cooperate with investigators.<ref name=\"2005attacks\" />\n\n==Aftermath==\nSinaga's father, Saibun Sinaga, in an interview with [[BBC]] Indonesia, expressed his opinion a day after the sentencing, where he was quoted as saying that his son \"got what he deserved\" and that \"we accept the verdict. His punishment fits his crimes. I don't want to discuss the case any further.\"<ref name=\"Fatherreaction\">{{cite web|last1=Nurdin|first1=Endang|last2=Henschke|first2=Rebecca|title=Reynhard Sinaga: Father of rapist says 'punishment fits his crimes'|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-51027404 |publisher=BBC News|date=7 January 2020|accessdate=7 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nSinaga's mother, Normawati Silaen, told ''[[The Sunday Times]]'' that she \"wondered if [Sinaga's final victim] had made up the story\". She stated that she was not aware that he was gay: \"We are a good Christian family who do not believe in homosexuality. He is my baby.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Reynhard Sinaga: Mother of Britain's most prolific rapist says he is still 'my baby' |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2020/01/12/reynhard-sinaga-mother-britains-prolific-rapist-says-still-baby/|work=The Sunday Telegraph|agency=[[PA Media]]|date=<!-- Sunday -->12 January 2020|access-date=12 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Collins|first=David|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/they-are-callling-him-the-worlds-worst-rapist-but-he-is-still-my-baby-hz8g338m2|title=Reynhard Sinaga's mother: the 'world's worst rapist' is still my baby|work=The Sunday Times|date=12 January 2020|access-date=12 January 2020}} {{subscription required}}</ref>\n\nThe charity Safeline reported a record increase in calls to its hotline for male sexual abuse survivors in the aftermath of the case, with Safeline founder Duncan Craig stating that it had started a national conversation regarding men opening up about sexual abuse.<ref name=\"hotline\"/>\n\nAfter Sinaga's conviction, the mayor of [[Depok]] in Indonesia, [[Mohammad Idris]], announced that he planned to order raids on the local [[LGBT rights in Indonesia|LGBT]] community.<ref>{{cite web|title=Indonesia rights body condemns LGBT raids ordered by mayor after UK rape case|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-indonesia-lgbt/indonesia-rights-body-condemns-lgbt-raids-ordered-by-mayor-after-uk-rape-case-idUSKBN1ZD0J6?il=0 |publisher=[[Reuters]]|first=Stanley|last=Widianto|date=14 January 2020|accessdate=14 January 2020}}</ref> The announcement was swiftly condemned by human rights activists saying that conservatives in Indonesia were using Sinaga as an excuse to target the gay community in the country.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Indonesia: LGBT community faces backlash after Reynhard Sinaga's rape conviction|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/jan/14/indonesia-lgbt-community-faces-backlash-after-reynhard-sinagas-conviction|first=Krithika|last=Varagur|publisher=[[The Guardian]]|date=14 January 2020|accessdate=16 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 January 2020, after Sinaga's case was referred by the Crown Prosecution Service to the [[Attorney General for England and Wales|Attorney General]], it was referred by him to the [[Court of Appeal (England and Wales)|Court of Appeal]] for being too lenient. [[Geoffrey Cox (British politician)|Geoffrey Cox]] was reported as saying a \"[[whole life order]]\" should be considered for Sinaga, meaning his crimes were so serious he would never be released from prison.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.sky.com/story/reynhard-sinaga-prolific-rapists-sentence-referred-for-being-too-lenient-11910022|title=Reynhard Sinaga: Prolific rapist should 'never be released', says Attorney General as he reviews sentence|website=Sky News}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/news/greater-manchester-news/reynhard-sinaga-court-of-appeal-17580075|title=Reynhard Sinaga's prison sentence could soon become 'whole life order'|first=Paul|last=Britton|date=16 January 2020|website=Manchester Evening News}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of serial rapists]]\n*[[Delroy Grant]]\n*[[Antoni Imiela]]\n*[[Joseph McCann (criminal)|Joseph McCann]]\n*[[Stephen Port]], serial killer who likewise drugged his male victims\n*[[Kirk Reid]]\n*[[John Worboys]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sinaga, Reynhard}}\n\n[[Category:1983 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:2010s trials]]\n[[Category:21st-century criminals]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of Leeds]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of Manchester]]\n[[Category:Gay men]]\n[[Category:Indonesian Christians]]\n[[Category:Indonesian criminals]]\n[[Category:Indonesian people imprisoned abroad]]\n[[Category:LGBT Christians]]\n[[Category:LGBT people from Indonesia]]\n[[Category:People convicted of attempted rape]]\n[[Category:People convicted of rape]]\n[[Category:People convicted of sexual assault]]\n[[Category:People from Jambi]]\n[[Category:People of Batak descent]]\n[[Category:Prisoners sentenced to life imprisonment by England and Wales]]\n[[Category:Rape in the 2010s]]\n[[Category:Rape of males]]\n[[Category:Rape trials]]\n[[Category:Trials in England]]\n[[Category:University of Indonesia alumni]]\n[[Category:Violence against men in the United Kingdom]]\n", "name_user": "2a02:c7f:c23f:2600:21a8:3bac:8f5a:e03e", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reynhard_Sinaga"}
{"title_page": "Mulan (2020 film)", "text_new": "{{short description|2020 film directed by Niki Caro}}\n{{Use American English|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Mulan\n| image          = Mulan (2020 film) poster.jpg\n| border         = no\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster with original release date\n| director       = [[Niki Caro]]\n| producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Chris Bender (film producer)|Chris Bender]]\n* Tendo Nagenda\n* Jason T. Reed\n* Jake Weiner\n}}\n| screenplay     = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Rick Jaffa and Amanda Silver|Rick Jaffa <br />Amanda Silver]]\n* Lauren Hynek\n* Elizabeth Martin\n}}\n| based on       = {{Plainlist|\n* {{based on|[[Walt Disney Animation Studios|Disney's]] ''[[Mulan (1998 film)|Mulan]]''|[[Tony Bancroft]]|[[Barry Cook]]}}\n* {{based on|[[Hua Mulan|''Ballad of Mulan'']]|[[Guo Maoqian]]}}\n}}\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Liu Yifei]]\n* [[Donnie Yen]]\n* [[Jason Scott Lee]]\n* [[Yoson An]]\n* [[Gong Li]]\n* [[Jet Li]] \n}}\n| music          = [[Harry Gregson-Williams]]<ref name=\"Gregson-Williams\">{{Cite web |url=http://filmmusicreporter.com/2018/08/22/harry-gregson-williams-to-score-disneys-mulan-live-action-movie/ |title=Harry-Gregson-Williams to Score Disney's 'Mulan' Live-Action Movie |website=Film Music Reporter |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180824135101/http://filmmusicreporter.com/2018/08/22/harry-gregson-williams-to-score-disneys-mulan-live-action-movie/ |archive-date=August 24, 2018 |access-date=August 24, 2018}}</ref>\n| cinematography = [[Mandy Walker]]\n| editing        = David Coulson\n| studio         = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Walt Disney Pictures]]\n* Jason T. Reed Productions\n* Good Fear\n}}\n| distributor    = [[Walt Disney Studios Motion Pictures]]\n| released       = {{Film date|2020|3|9|[[Hollywood]]|2020|7|24|United States}}\n| runtime        = \n| country        = United States\n| language       = English\n| budget         = $200  million<ref name=CNNbudget>{{Cite news |url= https://amp.cnn.com/cnn/2020/02/13/media/disney-mulan-coronavirus/index.html |title= Disney's 'Mulan' was supposed to be a big hit in China. The coronavirus could threaten that |last= Pallotta |first=Frank |date=February 14, 2020 |work=[[CNN Business]]|access-date=February 22, 2020}}</ref> \n| gross          = N/A<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/title/tt4566758/?ref_=bo_rl_ti | title=Mulan (2020) | work=[[Box Office Mojo]] | accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Mulan''''' is a 2020 American [[action drama]] film directed by [[Niki Caro]], with the screenplay by [[Rick Jaffa and Amanda Silver|Rick Jaffa, Amanda Silver]], Lauren Hynek, and Elizabeth Martin, produced by [[Walt Disney Pictures]], and distributed by [[Walt Disney Studios Motion Pictures]]. The film is based on the Chinese folklore \"The Ballad of [[Hua Mulan|Mulan]]\" and is a [[List of Disney live-action remakes of animated films|live-action adaptation]] of [[Walt Disney Animation Studios|Disney]]'s [[Mulan (1998 film)|1998 animated film of the same name]]. The film stars [[Liu Yifei]] in the [[Mulan (Disney character)|title role]], alongside [[Donnie Yen]], [[Jason Scott Lee]], [[Yoson An]], [[Gong Li]], and [[Jet Li]] in supporting roles.\n\nPlans for a live-action ''Mulan'' remake began in 2010, but the project never came to fruition. In March 2015, a new attempt was announced and Caro was hired to direct in February 2017. Liu was cast in the title role in November 2017, following a casting call of 1,000 actresses, and the rest of the cast joined over the following year. Filming began in August 2018 and lasted through November, taking place in [[New Zealand]] and [[China]].\n\n''Mulan'' is the first live-action remake from Disney to be given a PG-13 rating by the [[Motion Picture Association|MPAA]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2020/film/news/mulan-rating-pg-13-violence-disney-1203508059/|title=\u2018Mulan\u2019 Is Disney\u2019s First Live-Action Remake to Get a PG-13 Rating|last=Rico|first=Klaritza|date=2020-02-19|website=Variety|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref> It was scheduled to be released in the United States on March 27, 2020, but was delayed to July 24, 2020 due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]].\n\n==Premise==\n{{Quote|When the Emperor of China issues a decree that one man per family must serve in the Imperial Army to defend the country from Northern invaders, Hua Mulan, the eldest daughter of an honored warrior, steps in to take the place of her ailing father. Masquerading as a man, Hua Jun, she is tested every step of the way and must harness her inner-strength and embrace her true potential. It is an epic journey that will transform her into an honored warrior and earn her the respect of a grateful nation\u2026and a proud father.|source=[[Walt Disney Pictures]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://movies.disney.com/mulan-2020|title=Mulan (2020)|publisher=Disney Movies}}</ref>}}\n\n==Plot==\nThe original movie's plot will mostly be unchanged in the remake, with some exceptions. Mulan's original love interest, Captain Li Shang, was removed, with his role being spilt into two different characters,<ref>{{cite web|https://collider.com/mulan-changes-live-action-animated-version-disney/}}</ref> Commander Tung (Donnie Yen) and Chen Honghui (Yoson An). Also, Mushu, played by Eddie Murphy, was removed from the remake and a new character, Mulan's sister Hua Xiu, will be added. Finally, Shan Yu, the main antagonist of the original film, will not be in the remake. Instead, the main antagonist will be Xianniang, a shapeshifting witch who is an ally of Bori Khan.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Liu Yifei]] as [[Mulan (Disney character)|Mulan]], the eldest daughter of Hua Zhou who defies both tradition and the law by disguising herself as a man by the name of Hua Jun in order to enlist herself in the Imperial Army in place of her ailing father.<ref name=\"BBC\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-42177082 |title=Mulan: Disney casts Chinese actress Liu Yifei in lead role |date=November 30, 2017 |publisher=[[BBC]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180814004705/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-42177082 |archive-date=August 14, 2018 |access-date=July 21, 2018}}</ref>\n** Crystal Rao portrays a young Mulan.\n* [[Donnie Yen]] as [[List of Disney's Mulan characters#Commander Tung|Commander Tung]], the high ranking leader of the Imperial Army and mentor to Mulan.<ref name=\"Deadline1\">{{Cite news |url=https://deadline.com/2018/04/donnie-yen-mulan-disney-live-action-film-1202362542/ |title=Donnie Yen To Star In Disney's Live Action 'Mulan' |last=Fleming, Jr. |first=Mike |date=April 11, 2018 |work=Deadline |access-date=April 12, 2018 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180412082921/http://deadline.com/2018/04/donnie-yen-mulan-disney-live-action-film-1202362542/ |archive-date=April 12, 2018}}</ref> Both Tung and Chen are based on Li Shang from the animated film.<ref name=\"MulanOnSet\" />\n* [[Jason Scott Lee]] as [[List of Disney's Mulan characters#Shan Yu|Bori Khan]], a [[Rouran Khaganate|Rouran]]<ref name=\"MulanOnSet\" /> warrior leader intent on avenging his father's death. Khan is based on Shan Yu from the animated film.<ref name=\"HollywoodReporter1\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/disneys-mulan-adds-jason-scott-lee-1129918 |title=Disney's 'Mulan' Adds Jason Scott Lee |date=July 25, 2018 |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180726010208/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/disneys-mulan-adds-jason-scott-lee-1129918 |archive-date=July 26, 2018 |access-date=July 26, 2018}}</ref> \n* [[Yoson An]]<ref name=HollywoodReporter1/> as [[List of Disney's Mulan characters#Li Shang|Chen Honghui]], a confident and ambitious recruit who joins Commander Tung's unit, and becomes Mulan's ally and love interest.<ref name=\"HollywoodReporter2\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/mulan-disney-casts-yoson-an-as-love-interest-live-action-movie-1116949 |title=Disney Casts 'Mulan' Love Interest (Exclusive) |last=Ford |first=Rebecca |date=June 6, 2018 |work=The Hollywood Reporter |access-date=June 6, 2018 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180606230631/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/mulan-disney-casts-yoson-an-as-love-interest-live-action-movie-1116949 |archive-date=June 6, 2018}}</ref> Both Chen and Tung are based on Li Shang from the animated film.<ref name=\"MulanOnSet\" />\n*[[Gong Li]] as [[List of Disney's Mulan characters#Hayabusa|Xianniang]],<ref name=HollywoodReporter1/> a powerful [[Witchcraft|witch]] with [[shapeshifting]] abilities and an ally of Bori Khan.<ref name=\"HollywoodReporter3\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/disneys-live-action-mulan-lands-gong-li-jet-li-1101994 |title=Disney's Live-Action 'Mulan' Lands Gong Li, Jet Li (Exclusive) |last=Sun |first=Rebecca |date=April 12, 2018 |work=The Hollywood Reporter |access-date=April 14, 2018 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180413131542/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/disneys-live-action-mulan-lands-gong-li-jet-li-1101994 |archive-date=April 13, 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Jet Li]] as [[List of Disney's Mulan characters#The Emperor of China|The Emperor]] of China, a wise benevolent ruler of China who orders the mobilization of troops via the conscription of one man from each household to fight the Hun army.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/erikkain/2019/07/07/there-are-no-talking-dragons-or-singing-generals-in-this-live-action-mulan-trailer/#1f5fae1f5f0f |title=There Are No Talking Dragons Or Singing Generals In This Live-Action 'Mulan' Trailer |last=Kain, Erik |date=July 7, 2019 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190713050758/https://www.forbes.com/sites/erikkain/2019/07/07/there-are-no-talking-dragons-or-singing-generals-in-this-live-action-mulan-trailer/#1f5fae1f5f0f |archive-date=July 13, 2019 |access-date=July 13, 2019 |magazine=[[Forbes]]}}</ref>\n* [[Tzi Ma]] as [[List of Disney's Mulan characters#Fa Zhou|Hua Zhou]], Mulan's father and a famed [[Veteran|war veteran]], who is now recalled to the Imperial Army despite his frail health.<ref name=\"HuffPost\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.huffpost.com/entry/ming-na-wen-voice-of-animated-mulan-responds-to-new-teaser_n_5d267d35e4b0583e482badeb |title=Ming-Na Wen, Voice Of Animated Mulan, Responds To New Teaser |last=Yam, Kimberly |date=July 10, 2019 |publisher=[[HuffPost]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190713090948/https://www.huffpost.com/entry/ming-na-wen-voice-of-animated-mulan-responds-to-new-teaser_n_5d267d35e4b0583e482badeb |archive-date=July 13, 2019 |access-date=July 13, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Rosalind Chao]] as [[List of Disney's Mulan characters#Fa Li|Hua Li]], Mulan's mother and Zhou's wife.<ref name=HuffPost/>\n* Xana Tang as Hua Xiu, Mulan's younger sister.<ref name=HollywoodReporter3/> The character was added to the film's plot because the filmmakers felt that \"this added a broader emotional context and added more motivation for [Mulan's] character\".<ref name=\"MulanOnSet\"/>\n* [[Ron Yuan]] as Sergeant Qiang, the fiercely loyal second in command of the Imperial Regiment.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/05/mulan-utkarsh-ambudkar-ron-yuan-disney-1202396832/ |title='Mulan': Utkarsh Ambudkar & Ron Yuan Added To Disney's Live-Action Adaptation |last=N'Duka, Amanda |date=May 23, 2018 |publisher=Deadline |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190711104710/https://deadline.com/2018/05/mulan-utkarsh-ambudkar-ron-yuan-disney-1202396832/ |archive-date=July 11, 2019 |access-date=July 13, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Jimmy Wong]] as [[List of Disney's Mulan characters#Ling|Ling]], a recruit who joins Commander Tung's unit.<ref name=\"Deadline4\">{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/08/disney-mulan-jimmy-wong-doua-moua-1202445269/ |title=Disney's 'Mulan' Casts Jimmy Wong & Doua Moua |last=N'Duka |first=Amanda |date=August 14, 2018 |publisher=Deadline |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180814232736/https://deadline.com/2018/08/disney-mulan-jimmy-wong-doua-moua-1202445269/ |archive-date=August 14, 2018 |access-date=August 14, 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Doua Moua]] as [[List of Disney's Mulan characters#Chien-Po|Chien-Po]], a recruit who joins Commander Tung's unit.<ref name=Deadline4/>\n* [[Chen Tang (actor)|Chen Tang]] as [[List of Disney's Mulan characters#Yao|Yao]], a recruit who joins Commander Tung's unit.<ref name=\"Deadline5\">{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/09/adrian-martinez-disney-lady-and-the-tramp-mulan-chen-tang-1202469095/ |title=Adrian Martinez Joins Disney's 'Lady and the Tramp'; 'Mulan' Adds Chen Tang |last=N'Duka |first=Amanda |date=September 21, 2018 |publisher=Deadline |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180921230311/https://deadline.com/2018/09/adrian-martinez-disney-lady-and-the-tramp-mulan-chen-tang-1202469095/ |archive-date=September 21, 2018 |access-date=September 21, 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Nelson Lee]] as [[List of Disney's Mulan characters#Chi-Fu|The Chancellor]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://movieweb.com/mulan-2020-disney-remake-trailer-release-date/ |title=Disney's Mulan Remake Trailer Drops This Sunday |last=Sprague, Mike |date=July 6, 2019 |publisher=MovieWeb |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190708141758/https://movieweb.com/mulan-2020-disney-remake-trailer-release-date/ |archive-date=July 8, 2019 |access-date=July 13, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Cheng Pei-pei]]<ref name=Deadline3/> as [[List of Disney's Mulan characters|The Matchmaker]] \n* [[Utkarsh Ambudkar]] as Skatch, a con artist and friend of Ramtish.<ref name=HollywoodReporter2/>\n* Chum Ehelepola as Ramtish, a con artist and friend of Skatch.<ref name=HollywoodReporter2/>\n* Arka Das as Phoenix looks like a Mushu \n* Jun Yu as Cricket, an archer.<ref name=\"Liptak\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.theverge.com/2019/7/7/20685171/mulan-live-action-yifei-liu-niki-caro-animation-remake-first-trailer-watch |title=Watch the first trailer for Disney's live-action remake of Mulan |last=Liptak |first=Andrew |date=July 7, 2019 |website=[[The Verge]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190707165408/https://www.theverge.com/2019/7/7/20685171/mulan-live-action-yifei-liu-niki-caro-animation-remake-first-trailer-watch |archive-date=July 7, 2019 |access-date=July 7, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"MulanOnSet\">{{cite web|url=https://collider.com/mulan-changes-live-action-animated-version-disney/|title=\u2018Mulan\u2019: The Biggest Changes from the Animated Version in Disney\u2019s Live-Action Remake|website=Collider|last=Szany|first=Wendy Lee|date=February 27, 2020|accessdate=February 27, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Production==\n===Development===\n[[Walt Disney Pictures]] expressed interest in a [[List of Disney live-action remakes of animated films|live-action adaptation]] of the 1998 animated film ''[[Mulan (1998 film)|Mulan]]'' starring international star [[Zhang Ziyi]], with [[Chuck Russell]] chosen as the director. The film was originally planned to start filming in October 2010, but was canceled.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.channelnewsasia.com/stories/entertainment/view/1071985/1/.html |title=Zhang Ziyi to produce and star in 3D Mulan film |date=July 28, 2010 |website=[[Channel NewsAsia]] |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130318082003/http://www.channelnewsasia.com/stories/entertainment/view/1071985/1/.html |archive-date=March 18, 2013}}</ref> On March 30, 2015, ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' reported that Disney had restarted development of the live-action adaptation with [[Chris Bender (film producer)|Chris Bender]] and [[J. C. Spink]] producing, while Elizabeth Martin and Lauren Hynek would be writing the screenplay.<ref name=\"DevelopingMulan\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/disney-developing-live-action-mulan-784892/ |title=Disney Developing Live-Action 'Mulan' (Exclusive) |last=Ford |first=Rebecca |date=March 30, 2015 |website=The Hollywood Reporter |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150403121534/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/disney-developing-live-action-mulan-784892 |archive-date=April 3, 2015 |access-date=April 5, 2015}}</ref> On October 4, 2016, it was announced that [[Rick Jaffa and Amanda Silver]] would rewrite the script, combining the Chinese ballad and the 1998 animated film, while Jason T. Reed would be producing the film along with [[Chris Bender (film producer)|Chris Bender]] and Jake Weiner.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://variety.com/2016/film/news/mulan-release-date-live-action-disney-1201877832/ |title=Disney's Live-Action 'Mulan' to Hit Theaters in November 2018; Rick Jaffa and Amanda Silver Rewriting |last=Kroll |first=Justin |date=October 4, 2016 |work=Variety |access-date=October 5, 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161005192448/http://variety.com/2016/film/news/mulan-release-date-live-action-disney-1201877832/ |archive-date=October 5, 2016}}</ref> In February 27, 2020, Reed revealed that Mulan's sidekick from the original film, [[Mushu]], was removed due to the character's negative reception in China.<ref name=\"MulanOnSet\"/> Redd also said, aside from both the original ballad and the animated film, the filmmakers drew inspiration from different Chinese adaptations of the ballad while writing the film, stating that, since \"[t]he traditional Disney audience and the diaspora Asian audience viewed the movie in one way, and the traditional Chinese in China audience viewed a slightly different way\", the filmmakers \"dug in to try and make sure that [they are] addressing both of those audiences in a thoughtful way\".<ref name=\"MulanOnSet\"/>\n\n===Casting===\n[[File:Liu Yifei at the 2016 BAZAAR Stars\u2019 Charity Night.jpg|thumb|upright|Liu Yifei plays Mulan in the remake.]]\nSince several recent Hollywood films were accused of [[Whitewashing in film|whitewashing]], ''Mulan'' has been under intense scrutiny since ''The Hollywood Reporter'' reported that Disney was making a live-action adaptation of ''[[Mulan (1998 film)|Mulan]]''. An [[online petition]] titled \"Tell Disney You Don't Want A Whitewashed Mulan!\" received more than 100,000 signatures.<ref name=BBC/> On October 4, 2016, Disney announced that a global search for a Chinese actress to portray the title role was underway.<ref name=\"FindingMulan\">{{Cite news|last=McClintock |first=Pamela |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/disneys-live-action-mulan-gets-934976 |title=Disney's Live-Action 'Mulan' Gets Winter 2018 Release Date |date=October 4, 2016 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180618014152/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/disneys-live-action-mulan-gets-934976 |archive-date=June 18, 2018 |access-date=June 22, 2018}}</ref> A team of casting directors visited five continents and saw nearly 1,000 candidates for the role with criteria that required credible martial arts skills, the ability to speak clear English, and star quality.<ref name=\"YifeiCast\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/disneys-mulan-finds-star-1061585 |title=Disney's 'Mulan' Finds Its Star (Exclusive) |last=Sun |first=Rebecca |date=November 29, 2017 |work=The Hollywood Reporter |access-date=January 17, 2018 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201044128/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/disneys-mulan-finds-star-1061585?utm_source=twitter |archive-date=December 1, 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn November 29, 2017, Chinese-American actress [[Liu Yifei]] was cast in the film to portray the titular role of Mulan. Many celebrated this as a win for diversity in Disney films.<ref name=BBC/> Further cast announcements for [[Donnie Yen]], [[Gong Li]], [[Jet Li]], and Xana Tang were made in April 2018,<ref name=Deadline1/><ref name=HollywoodReporter3/> [[Utkarsh Ambudkar]] and [[Ron Yuan]] in May,<ref name=\"AmbudkarYuanCast\">{{Cite news |url=https://deadline.com/2018/05/mulan-utkarsh-ambudkar-ron-yuan-disney-1202396832/ |title='Mulan': Utkarsh Ambudkar & Ron Yuan Added To Disney's Live-Action Adaptation |last=N'Duka |first=Amanda |date=May 23, 2018 |work=Deadline |access-date=May 24, 2018 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180524151432/http://deadline.com/2018/05/mulan-utkarsh-ambudkar-ron-yuan-disney-1202396832/ |archive-date=May 24, 2018}}</ref> [[Yoson An]] and Chum Ehelepola in June,<ref name=HollywoodReporter2/> [[Jason Scott Lee]] in July,<ref name=HollywoodReporter1/> [[Tzi Ma]], [[Rosalind Chao]], [[Cheng Pei-Pei]], [[Nelson Lee]], [[Jimmy Wong]] and [[Doua Moua]] in August,<ref name=\"Deadline3\">{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/08/mulan-production-starting-new-cast-disney-1202444587/ |title='Mulan' Rounds Out Cast, Reveals First-Look Photo As Filming Underway On Live-Action Movie |last=Hipes |first=Patrick |date=August 13, 2018 |publisher=Deadline |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180813184830/https://deadline.com/2018/08/mulan-production-starting-new-cast-disney-1202444587/ |archive-date=August 13, 2018 |access-date=August 13, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Deadline4\"/> and [[Chen Tang (actor)|Chen Tang]] in September.<ref name=Deadline5/>\n\n===Director===\nDisney originally sought an Asian director. Disney first considered [[Ang Lee]], Taiwanese film director and two-time [[Academy Award]] winner for [[Academy Award for Best Director|Best Director]]. ''The Hollywood Reporter'' mentioned that Lee was approached but declined on October 12, 2016.<ref name=\"LeePass\">{{Cite news|last=Ford|first=Rebecca|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/mulan-mania-disney-sony-hunt-937274 |title='Mulan' Mania: Disney, Sony Hunt for Asian Directors to Helm Rival Action Pics |date=October 12, 2016 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180814001804/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/mulan-mania-disney-sony-hunt-937274 |archive-date=August 14, 2018 |access-date=June 22, 2018}}</ref> According to the report, published on November 22, 2016, he said that he would like to see an Asian director leading the film, but he himself had to decline because he was still obliged to promote his film ''[[Billy Lynn's Long Halftime Walk (film)|Billy Lynn's Long Halftime Walk]]''.<ref name=\"LeeSaid\">{{Cite news |last=Lee |first=Ashley |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/rambling-reporter/ang-lee-disneys-live-action-mulan-itd-be-great-see-an-asian-director-949162 |title=Ang Lee on Disney's Live-Action 'Mulan': \"It'd Be Great to See an Asian\" Director |date=November 22, 2016 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180814001739/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/rambling-reporter/ang-lee-disneys-live-action-mulan-itd-be-great-see-an-asian-director-949162 |archive-date=August 14, 2018 |access-date=June 22, 2018}}</ref> Next, Disney met with [[Jiang Wen]] for the position; finally on February 14, 2017, [[Niki Caro]] was hired as the director of the film, which made ''Mulan'' the second Disney film with a female director and a budget above $100 million following ''[[A Wrinkle in Time (2018 film)|A Wrinkle in Time]]''.<ref name=\"NikiHelm\">{{Cite news |last=Sun |first=Rebecca |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/disneys-live-action-mulan-finds-director-975869 |title=Disney's Live-Action 'Mulan' Finds Director (Exclusive) |work=The Hollywood Reporter |access-date=February 16, 2017 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170216072040/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/disneys-live-action-mulan-finds-director-975869 |archive-date=February 16, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Filming===\n[[Principal photography]] began on August 13, 2018, at different locations in New Zealand and China and [[Wrap (filmmaking)|wrapped]] on November 25, 2018.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://omegaunderground.com/2018/04/12/update-disney-to-begin-shooting-mulan-this-august-in-new-zealand-and-china/ |title=UPDATE: Disney To Begin Shooting 'Mulan' This August In New Zealand and China - Omega Underground |last=Marc |first=Christopher |date=April 12, 2018 |work=omegaunderground.com |access-date=April 12, 2018 |archive-date=August 16, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180816062124/https://thegww.com/update-disney-to-begin-shooting-mulan-this-august-in-new-zealand-and-china/}}</ref><ref name=Deadline3/> According to actress [[Gong Li]], the film's production budget was $290\u2013300 million due to the \"massive and...unprecedented scale\" of the sets,<ref name=\"GongLiBudget\">{{Cite web |url=https://heroichollywood.com/mulan-disney-li-gong-budget/ |title=Gong Li Claims Live-Action 'Mulan' Budget Is More Than $300 Million |last=Caesar Galvin |date=May 19, 2019 |website=Heroic Hollywood |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190718220408/https://heroichollywood.com/mulan-disney-li-gong-budget/ |archive-date=July 18, 2019 |access-date=July 19, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"GongLiBudget2\">{{Cite web |last=Bonomolo |first=Cameron |url=https://comicbook.com/movies/2018/05/07/disney-live-action-mulan-budget-most-expensive-movies-ever-made/ |title=Disney's Live-Action 'Mulan' Budget Makes It One of the Most Expensive Movies Ever Made |date=May 8, 2019 |website=ComicBook.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190718183231/https://comicbook.com/movies/2018/05/07/disney-live-action-mulan-budget-most-expensive-movies-ever-made/ |archive-date=July 18, 2019 |access-date=July 19, 2019}}</ref> although the actual figure was later reported to be $200 million.<ref name=CNNbudget/><ref>{{cite news|last=Ford|first=Rebecca|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/features/inside-disneys-bold-200m-gamble-mulan-stakes-couldnt-be-higher-1280999|title=Inside Disney's Bold $200M Gamble on 'Mulan': \"The Stakes Couldn't Be Higher\"|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=February 26, 2020|access-date=February 26, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Post-production===\nThe visual effects are provided by [[Sony Pictures Imageworks]], [[Weta Digital]], [[Framestore]], and [[Image Engine]], with Seth Maury and [[Anders Langlands|Andres Langlands]] serving as visual effects supervisors and [[Sean Andrew Faden]] serving as production supervisor.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.artofvfx.com/mulan/ |title=Mulan - ART OF VFX |date=July 8, 2019 |website=www.artofvfx.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190708122921/https://www.artofvfx.com/mulan/ |archive-date=July 8, 2019 |access-date=July 8, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Music===\nDirector [[Niki Caro]] revealed that the remake won't feature any songs from the original film;<ref>{{Cite web |last=Taylor |first=Drew |url=https://www.moviefone.com/2017/03/17/mulan-exclusive-niki-caro/ |title=Exclusive: 'Mulan' Director Niki Caro Says No Songs in the Upcoming Remake |date=March 17, 2018 |website=MovieFone |url-status=live |access-date=January 13, 2020}}</ref> the film instead will feature instrumental versions of the original film's songs.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Colon |first=Jessenika |url=https://thedisinsider.com/2019/06/29/exclusive-phoenix-possibly-replacing-mushu-in-mulan-cast-will-not-sing-classic-songs/ |title=EXCLUSIVE: Phoenix Possibly Replacing Mushu in 'Mulan'; Cast Will Not Sing Classic Songs |date=June 30, 2019|website=www.thedisinsider.com |url-status=live |access-date=January 13, 2020}}</ref> Caro later explained that the songs were deleted because she felt it didn't fit with her realistic vision of the film; she believes that since people do not break out into song as they enter war, the film should not either. Though she still tried to \"honour the music from the animation in a very significant way\",<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/benhenry/mulan-director-niki-caro-q-and-a|title=The Director Of \"Mulan\" Just Revealed Why There Won't Be Any Songs In Disney's Live-Action Remake|date=January 13, 2020|website=BuzzFeed|url-status=live|access-date=January 13, 2020}}</ref> she did not want to disrespect the original film in any way; however, she claimed she could not find a place to squeeze in the original music. Producer Jason T. Reed clarified Caro's previous statement by saying that the songs will be featured \"in a slightly different way\" in the remake.<ref name=\"MulanOnSet\"/>\n\n[[Harry Gregson-Williams]], who previously worked with Caro on ''[[The Zookeeper's Wife (film)|The Zookeeper's Wife]]'', composed the film's score.<ref name=\"Gregson-Williams\"/>\n\n[[Matthew Wilder]], who previously co-wrote the songs for the original film, revealed that the remake will feature a new version of the song \"[[Reflection (song)|Reflection]]\", and that the song \"thematically plays a large part in the new movie throughout the score\".<ref>{{Cite web |last=Shuler |first=Skyler |url=https://thedisinsider.com/2020/02/13/matthew-wilder-reflection-mulan/ |title=Songwriter Matthew Wilder Discusses \"Reflection\" In Disney\u2019s \u2018Mulan\u2019 |date=February 13, 2020|website=www.thedisinsider.com |url-status=live |access-date=February 27, 2020}}</ref> [[Christina Aguilera]], who previously performed an end-credits version of \"Reflection\" for the original film, confirmed during a performance in [[The Xperience]] that she had recorded a new version of \"Reflection\", as well as new material for the remake's soundtrack.<ref>{{cite news |last=Lenker |first=Maureen Lee |url=https://ew.com/movies/christina-aguilera-new-mulan-music/ |title=Original 'Reflection' singer Christina Aguilera has recorded new material for live-action Mulan |work=Entertainment Weekly |date=February 27, 2020 |accessdate=March 4, 2020}}</ref> On March 6, 2020, she released a new single for the film's soundtrack, titled \"Loyal Brave True\". The song was written by Jamie Hartman, Harry Gregson-Williams, Rosi Golan and Billy Crabtree, and produced by Jamie Hartman. The song was also released in Spanish, as \u201cEl Mejor Guerrero.\u201d Additionally, the singer confirmed that she would also release a re-recorded version of \"Reflection\".\n<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.thedigitalfix.com/music/new-music/christina-aguilera-shares-her-track-loyal-brave-true-taken-from-the-upcoming-disney-remake-of-mulan/ |title=Christina Aguilera shares her track, 'Loyal Brave True', taken from the upcoming Disney remake of Mulan|website=The Digital Fix |date=March 6, 2020}}</ref>\n<ref>{{cite news|first=Joey|last=Nolfi|url=https://ew.com/movies/christina-aguilera-new-song-loyal-brave-true-mulan/|title=Hear Christina Aguilera's warrior spirit on new Mulan ballad 'Loyal Brave True'|work=Entertainment Weekly|date=March 6, 2020|accessdate=March 6, 2020}}</ref> On March 8, a [[Mandarin Chinese|Mandarin]]-version of the song performed by Liu Yifei was released.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.chinadaily.com.cn/a/202003/09/WS5e65cb3ca31012821727d709.html|title=Chinese version of 'Reflection' released for upcoming 'Mulan' - Chinadaily.com.cn|last=\u987e\u99a8|website=www.chinadaily.com.cn|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref> Liu's interpretation is a revisitation of the Mandarin-language version of Aguilera's song, originally performed for the animated movie by [[Hong Kong]]-[[Chinese Americans|Chinese American]] singer [[Coco Lee]], who also voiced Mulan in the [[Taiwanese Mandarin]] dubbing in 1998.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=f7Z6FhaAPFI|title=\u674e\u739f CoCo Lee - \u81ea\u5df1|last=|first=|date=|website=YouTube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://disneyinternationalvoices.weebly.com/mulan.html|title=Mulan|website=CHARGUIGOU|language=fr|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref>\n\n==Marketing==\nOn July 7, 2019, the official teaser trailer and the official teaser poster were released during the broadcast of the [[2019 FIFA Women's World Cup Final]].<ref name=\"Liptak\"/> The teaser trailer was viewed 175.1 million times in its first 24 hours, including 52 million from China, making it [[List of most-viewed online videos in the first 24 hours#Top trailers|the seventh most viewed trailer in that time period]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/07/mulan-teaser-trailer-175-million-views-24-hours-china-worldwide-disney-1202643480/ |title='Mulan' Teaser Trailer Logs Epic 175M+ Views In First 24 Hours, Including 52M From China |last=Tartaglione |first=Nancy |date=July 9, 2019 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190827031552/https://deadline.com/2019/07/mulan-teaser-trailer-175-million-views-24-hours-china-worldwide-disney-1202643480/ |archive-date=August 27, 2019 |access-date=December 6, 2019}}</ref> On September 30, an exclusive photo featuring Liu as a soldier in the Imperial Army was released on Empire's upcoming ''[[Star Wars: The Rise of Skywalker]]'' issue.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.empireonline.com/movies/news/mulan-disney-remake-david-lean-akira-kurosawa/ |title=Mulan Live-Action Remake Taking 'David Lean Or Kurosawa Approach'- Exclusive Image |last=Travis |first=Ben |date=September 30, 2019 |website=[[Empire (magazine)|Empire]] |access-date=September 30, 2019}}</ref> On October 24, a prequel novel written by writer [[Grace Lin]] was announced along with a preview being made available online. Entitled ''Mulan: Before the Sword'', the novel was announced to be released on February 11, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://ew.com/books/2019/10/24/grace-lin-mulan-novel-cover-excerpt/ |title=Exclusive preview: Grace Lin fashions a gorgeous original Mulan novel |last=Canfield |first=David |date=October 29, 2019 |website=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |access-date=February 17, 2020}}</ref> On November 4, a video clip filmed during a Toho cinema preview was leaked online, featuring new shots of Mulan as a warrior battling fiercely and taking off her hair band.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://tieba.baidu.com/p/6324507746/ |title=New shots and new lines from Mulan |date=November 4, 2019 |website=[[Baidu]] |access-date=November 4, 2019}}</ref> On November 6, Liu was featured as one of the 25 stars of Next Gen Talent 2019 nominated by ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' with two new studio stills released concurrently.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/next-gen-talent-2019-hollywoods-rising-young-stars-revealed-1250276/ |title=Next Gen Talent 2019: Hollywood's Rising Young Stars Revealed |last=Elise Sandberg |first=Bryn |date=November 6, 2019 |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |access-date=November 6, 2019}}</ref> On November 20, the Japanese theatrical poster was released online.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.reddit.com/r/movies/comments/dz0cjv/japanese_poster_of_disneys_liveaction_movie_mulan/ |title=Japanese Poster of Disney's live-action movie Mulan |date=November 20, 2019 |website=[[Reddit]] |access-date=November 20, 2019}}</ref> On December 5, the official trailer was released with dual versions: the Chinese Weibo debuted a shorter version with different cut and a few shots that were not featured in the US version.{{citation needed|date=January 2020}} On January 26, 2020, 6 individual character posters were released.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://collider.com/mulan-character-posters-liu-yifei-donnie-yen/#mulan-character-poster-liu-yifei|title=These New 'Mulan' Character Posters Will Make a Fan Out of You|first=Allie|last=Gemmill|work=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]|date=January 26, 2020|accessdate=February 23, 2020}}</ref> On February 2, 2020, the final trailer was released.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thewrap.com/mulan-final-trailer-puts-villains-in-the-spotlight-video/|title=\u2018Mulan': Final Trailer Puts Villains in the Spotlight (Video)|first=Jeremy|last=Fuster|work=[[The Wrap]]|date=March 10, 2020|accessdate=February 2, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Release==\n''Mulan'' had its world premiere at the [[Dolby Theatre]] in Hollywood on March 9, 2020.<ref>{{Cite news |url= https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/mulan-first-reactions-premiere-1283199 |title= 'Mulan': First Reactions from the Premiere |date=March 9, 2020 |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |access-date=March 10, 2020}}</ref> It had been originally set for a November 2, 2018, release but was delayed, with ''[[The Nutcracker and the Four Realms]]'' taking its slot.<ref name=\"FindingMulan\" /> It was then scheduled to be released in the United States on March 27, 2020,<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/mulan-reboot-release-date-pushed-back-1202714825/ |title='Mulan' Live-Action Reboot Pushed Back to 2020 |last=Khatchatourian |first=Maane |date=March 1, 2018 |work=Variety |access-date=March 1, 2018 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180302162410/http://variety.com/2018/film/news/mulan-reboot-release-date-pushed-back-1202714825/ |archive-date=March 2, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"NewRelease\">{{Cite news |last1=McClintock |first1=Pamela |last2=Couch |first2=Aaron |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/live-action-mulan-pushed-back-more-a-year-spring-2020-1090015 |title=Live-Action 'Mulan' Pushed Back More Than a Year to Spring 2020 |date=March 1, 2018 |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180616053315/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/live-action-mulan-pushed-back-more-a-year-spring-2020-1090015 |archive-date=June 16, 2018 |access-date=June 21, 2018}}</ref> but was delayed again due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/mulan-release-pushed-back-coronavirus-pandemic-1284275|title='Mulan' Release Pushed Back Amid Coronavirus Pandemic|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|first=Mia|last=Galuppo|date=March 12, 2020|accessdate=March 12, 2020}}</ref> The film is scheduled to be released on July 24, 2020, taking the former slot of ''[[Jungle Cruise (film)|Jungle Cruise]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/black-widow-mulan-nab-new-release-dates-jungle-cruise-delayed-a-year-1286854|title='Black Widow,' 'Mulan' Land New 2020 Release Dates, 'Jungle Cruise' Delayed a Year|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|first=Pamela |last=McClintock  |archive-date= April 3, 2020|access-date=April 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Controversies ==\nA call to boycott the film began when Liu Yifei reshared an image posted by Chinese newspaper ''[[People's Daily]]''. The image included a quote from Chinese reporter [[List of August 2019 Hong Kong protests#12\u201314 August police brutality protests|Fu Guohao]] who worked for the ''[[Global Times]]'' and was subsequently assaulted by protesters during the [[2019 Hong Kong anti-extradition bill protests]]: \"I support Hong Kong police. You can beat me now. What a shame for Hong Kong.\" This sparked international controversy, with Liu being accused of supporting [[police brutality]]. The hashtag, #BoycottMulan, has since started trending supporting a boycott of the movie.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Ramzy |first=Austin |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/08/14/world/asia/hong-kong-airport-protests.html |title=Soul Searching Among Hong Kong Protesters After Chaos at Airport |date=August 14, 2019 |work=[[The New York Times]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190818034516/https://www.nytimes.com/2019/08/14/world/asia/hong-kong-airport-protests.html |archive-date=August 18, 2019 |access-date=August 16, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Yeung |first=Jessie |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2019/08/16/asia/china-mulan-actor-protests-intl-hnk-trnd/index.html |title=Hong Kong protesters call for 'Mulan' boycott after star went public in support of police |date=August 16, 2019 |website=[[CNN]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190818081756/https://edition.cnn.com/2019/08/16/asia/china-mulan-actor-protests-intl-hnk-trnd/index.html |archive-date=August 18, 2019 |access-date=August 16, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-49373276 |title=Liu Yifei: Mulan boycott urged after star backs HK police |date=August 16, 2019 |website=[[BBC]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190818003707/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-49373276 |archive-date=August 18, 2019 |access-date=August 16, 2019}}</ref> In response to the controversy, Liu was not present at the 2019 [[D23 Expo]], which gave fans an exclusive sneak peek of the film.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/mulan-cast-d23-boycottmulan-1203311115/ |title='Mulan' Star Crystal Yifei Liu Skips D23 Amid International Controversy |last=Nissen |first=Dano |date=August 24, 2019 |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |access-date=October 26, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn February 27, 2020, film producer Jason T. Reed said that Mulan's love interest [[List of Disney's Mulan characters#Li Shang|Captain Li Shang]] was dropped in response to the [[Me Too movement]]. In his statement, he explained that \"having a commanding officer that is also the sexual love interest was very uncomfortable and we didn\u2019t think it was appropriate\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://collider.com/mulan-li-shang-not-in-live-action-remake-reason-why/|title='Mulan': Why Captain Li Shang Isn't in the Live-Action Remake|last=Szany|first=Wendy Lee|work=Collider|date=February 27, 2020|access-date=March 2, 2020}}</ref> The reasoning behind the removal was met with social media backlash from fans of the original film and members of the [[LGBTQ]] community, who deemed Shang's relationship with Mulan's male [[alter ego]] Ping to be [[bisexual]].<ref name=\"Forbes\">{{cite news|last=Maleh|first=Linda|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/lindamaleh/2020/02/28/disney-blames-metoo-for-li-shangs-absence-from-mulan-in-new-controversy/#2c41d8e95965|title=Disney Blames #MeToo For Li Shang's Absence From 'Mulan' In New Controversy|work=Forbes|date=February 28, 2020|accessdate=March 2, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-51707188|title=Mulan: Disney drop character following #MeToo movement|publisher=BBC News|date=March 2, 2020|accessdate=March 2, 2020}}</ref> Reed was initially surprised by criticism of Shang's removal, but acknowledged that the character had become a \"LGBTQ icon\",<ref name=\"Vogue\">{{cite news|last=Rearick|first=Lauren|url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/mulan-love-interest-li-shang-reportedly-split-two-characters-metoo|title=Mulan\" Love Interest Li Shang Was Reportedly Split Into Two Characters Because of MeToo|work=Teen Vogue|date=February 28, 2020|accessdate=March 2, 2020}}</ref> and clarified that Shang's role would be served by two new characters, Commander Tung and Chen Honghui.<ref name=\"Forbes\"/><ref name=\"Vogue\"/>\n\n==Sequel==\nIn April 2020, it was announced that a ''Mulan'' sequel is in development at Disney with Chris Bender, Jason T. Reed and Jake Weiner returning as producers for sequel.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://fullcirclecinema.com/2020/04/18/mulan-2-early-development-disney/|title=\u2018Mulan 2\u2019 Reportedly In Early Development At Disney|magazine=Full Circle Cinema|last=Campbell|first=Jacob|date=April 18, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|https://movies.disney.com/mulan-2020}}\n* {{IMDb title|4566758}}\n\n{{Disney's Mulan}}\n{{Disney Princess}}\n{{Disney's live-action adaptations of animated franchises}}\n{{Niki Caro}}\n{{Rick Jaffa and Amanda Silver}}\n\n[[Category:2020 3D films]]\n[[Category:2020s action drama films]]\n[[Category:2020s fantasy films]]\n[[Category:2020s feminist films]]\n[[Category:American 3D films]]\n[[Category:American action adventure films]]\n[[Category:American action films]]\n[[Category:American adventure films]]\n[[Category:American fantasy adventure films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American martial arts films]]\n[[Category:American war films]]\n[[Category:Cross-dressing in American films]]\n[[Category:Disney film remakes]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Film remakes]]\n[[Category:Films about sexism]]\n[[Category:Films about witchcraft]]\n[[Category:Films based on adaptations]]\n[[Category:Films based on multiple works]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Niki Caro]]\n[[Category:Films postponed due to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Harry Gregson-Williams]]\n[[Category:Films set in Imperial China]]\n[[Category:Films shot in China]]\n[[Category:Films shot in New Zealand]]\n[[Category:Films with screenplays by Rick Jaffa and Amanda Silver]]\n[[Category:IMAX films]]\n[[Category:Mulan (franchise)]]\n[[Category:Period action films]]\n[[Category:Upcoming IMAX films]]\n[[Category:Walt Disney Pictures films]]\n[[Category:War adventure films]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2020 film directed by Niki Caro}}\n{{Use American English|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Mulan\n| image          = Mulan (2020 film) poster.jpg\n| border         = no\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster with original release date\n| director       = [[Niki Caro]]\n| producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Chris Bender (film producer)|Chris Bender]]\n* Tendo Nagenda\n* Jason T. Reed\n* Jake Weiner\n}}\n| screenplay     = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Rick Jaffa and Amanda Silver|Rick Jaffa <br />Amanda Silver]]\n* Lauren Hynek\n* Elizabeth Martin\n}}\n| based on       = {{Plainlist|\n* {{based on|[[Walt Disney Animation Studios|Disney's]] ''[[Mulan (1998 film)|Mulan]]''|[[Tony Bancroft]]|[[Barry Cook]]}}\n* {{based on|[[Hua Mulan|''Ballad of Mulan'']]|[[Guo Maoqian]]}}\n}}\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Liu Yifei]]\n* [[Donnie Yen]]\n* [[Jason Scott Lee]]\n* [[Yoson An]]\n* [[Gong Li]]\n* [[Jet Li]] \n}}\n| music          = [[Harry Gregson-Williams]]<ref name=\"Gregson-Williams\">{{Cite web |url=http://filmmusicreporter.com/2018/08/22/harry-gregson-williams-to-score-disneys-mulan-live-action-movie/ |title=Harry-Gregson-Williams to Score Disney's 'Mulan' Live-Action Movie |website=Film Music Reporter |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180824135101/http://filmmusicreporter.com/2018/08/22/harry-gregson-williams-to-score-disneys-mulan-live-action-movie/ |archive-date=August 24, 2018 |access-date=August 24, 2018}}</ref>\n| cinematography = [[Mandy Walker]]\n| editing        = David Coulson\n| studio         = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Walt Disney Pictures]]\n* Jason T. Reed Productions\n* Good Fear\n}}\n| distributor    = [[Walt Disney Studios Motion Pictures]]\n| released       = {{Film date|2020|3|9|[[Hollywood]]|2020|7|24|United States}}\n| runtime        = \n| country        = United States\n| language       = English\n| budget         = $200  million<ref name=CNNbudget>{{Cite news |url= https://amp.cnn.com/cnn/2020/02/13/media/disney-mulan-coronavirus/index.html |title= Disney's 'Mulan' was supposed to be a big hit in China. The coronavirus could threaten that |last= Pallotta |first=Frank |date=February 14, 2020 |work=[[CNN Business]]|access-date=February 22, 2020}}</ref> \n| gross          = N/A<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/title/tt4566758/?ref_=bo_rl_ti | title=Mulan (2020) | work=[[Box Office Mojo]] | accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Mulan''''' is a 2020 American [[action drama]] film directed by [[Niki Caro]], with the screenplay by [[Rick Jaffa and Amanda Silver|Rick Jaffa, Amanda Silver]], Lauren Hynek, and Elizabeth Martin, produced by [[Walt Disney Pictures]], and distributed by [[Walt Disney Studios Motion Pictures]]. The film is based on the Chinese folklore \"The Ballad of [[Hua Mulan|Mulan]]\" and is a [[List of Disney live-action remakes of animated films|live-action adaptation]] of [[Walt Disney Animation Studios|Disney]]'s [[Mulan (1998 film)|1998 animated film of the same name]]. The film stars [[Liu Yifei]] in the [[Mulan (Disney character)|title role]], alongside [[Donnie Yen]], [[Jason Scott Lee]], [[Yoson An]], [[Gong Li]], and [[Jet Li]] in supporting roles.\n\nPlans for a live-action ''Mulan'' remake began in 2010, but the project never came to fruition. In March 2015, a new attempt was announced and Caro was hired to direct in February 2017. Liu was cast in the title role in November 2017, following a casting call of 1,000 actresses, and the rest of the cast joined over the following year. Filming began in August 2018 and lasted through November, taking place in [[New Zealand]] and [[China]].\n\n''Mulan'' is the first live-action remake from Disney to be given a PG-13 rating by the [[Motion Picture Association|MPAA]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2020/film/news/mulan-rating-pg-13-violence-disney-1203508059/|title=\u2018Mulan\u2019 Is Disney\u2019s First Live-Action Remake to Get a PG-13 Rating|last=Rico|first=Klaritza|date=2020-02-19|website=Variety|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref> It was scheduled to be released in the United States on March 27, 2020, but was delayed to July 24, 2020 due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]].\n\n==Premise==\n{{Quote|When the Emperor of China issues a decree that one man per family must serve in the Imperial Army to defend the country from Northern invaders, Hua Mulan, the eldest daughter of an honored warrior, steps in to take the place of her ailing father. Masquerading as a man, Hua Jun, she is tested every step of the way and must harness her inner-strength and embrace her true potential. It is an epic journey that will transform her into an honored warrior and earn her the respect of a grateful nation\u2026and a proud father.|source=[[Walt Disney Pictures]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://movies.disney.com/mulan-2020|title=Mulan (2020)|publisher=Disney Movies}}</ref>}}\n\n==Plot==\nThe original movie's plot will mostly be unchanged in the remake, with some exceptions. Mulan's original love interest, Captain Li Shang, was removed, with his role being spilt into two different characters,<ref>{{cite web|https://collider.com/mulan-changes-live-action-animated-version-disney/}}</ref> Commander Tung (Donnie Yen) and Chen Honghui (Yoson An). Also, Mushu, played by Eddie Murphy, was removed from the remake and a new character, Mulan's sister Hua Xiu, will be added. Finally, Shan Yu, the main antagonist of the original film, will not be in the remake. Instead, the main antagonist will be Xianniang, a shapeshifting witch who is an ally of Bori Khan.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Liu Yifei]] as [[Mulan (Disney character)|Mulan]], the eldest daughter of Hua Zhou who defies both tradition and the law by disguising herself as a man by the name of Hua Jun in order to enlist herself in the Imperial Army in place of her ailing father.<ref name=\"BBC\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-42177082 |title=Mulan: Disney casts Chinese actress Liu Yifei in lead role |date=November 30, 2017 |publisher=[[BBC]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180814004705/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-42177082 |archive-date=August 14, 2018 |access-date=July 21, 2018}}</ref>\n** Crystal Rao portrays a young Mulan.\n* [[Donnie Yen]] as [[List of Disney's Mulan characters#Commander Tung|Commander Tung]], the high ranking leader of the Imperial Army and mentor to Mulan.<ref name=\"Deadline1\">{{Cite news |url=https://deadline.com/2018/04/donnie-yen-mulan-disney-live-action-film-1202362542/ |title=Donnie Yen To Star In Disney's Live Action 'Mulan' |last=Fleming, Jr. |first=Mike |date=April 11, 2018 |work=Deadline |access-date=April 12, 2018 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180412082921/http://deadline.com/2018/04/donnie-yen-mulan-disney-live-action-film-1202362542/ |archive-date=April 12, 2018}}</ref> Both Tung and Chen are based on Li Shang from the animated film.<ref name=\"MulanOnSet\" />\n* [[Jason Scott Lee]] as [[List of Disney's Mulan characters#Shan Yu|Bori Khan]], a [[Rouran Khaganate|Rouran]]<ref name=\"MulanOnSet\" /> warrior leader intent on avenging his father's death. Khan is based on Shan Yu from the animated film.<ref name=\"HollywoodReporter1\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/disneys-mulan-adds-jason-scott-lee-1129918 |title=Disney's 'Mulan' Adds Jason Scott Lee |date=July 25, 2018 |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180726010208/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/disneys-mulan-adds-jason-scott-lee-1129918 |archive-date=July 26, 2018 |access-date=July 26, 2018}}</ref> \n* [[Yoson An]]<ref name=HollywoodReporter1/> as [[List of Disney's Mulan characters#Li Shang|Chen Honghui]], a confident and ambitious recruit who joins Commander Tung's unit, and becomes Mulan's ally and love interest.<ref name=\"HollywoodReporter2\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/mulan-disney-casts-yoson-an-as-love-interest-live-action-movie-1116949 |title=Disney Casts 'Mulan' Love Interest (Exclusive) |last=Ford |first=Rebecca |date=June 6, 2018 |work=The Hollywood Reporter |access-date=June 6, 2018 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180606230631/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/mulan-disney-casts-yoson-an-as-love-interest-live-action-movie-1116949 |archive-date=June 6, 2018}}</ref> Both Chen and Tung are based on Li Shang from the animated film.<ref name=\"MulanOnSet\" />\n*[[Gong Li]] as [[List of Disney's Mulan characters#Hayabusa|Xianniang]],<ref name=HollywoodReporter1/> a powerful [[Witchcraft|witch]] with [[shapeshifting]] abilities and an ally of Bori Khan.<ref name=\"HollywoodReporter3\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/disneys-live-action-mulan-lands-gong-li-jet-li-1101994 |title=Disney's Live-Action 'Mulan' Lands Gong Li, Jet Li (Exclusive) |last=Sun |first=Rebecca |date=April 12, 2018 |work=The Hollywood Reporter |access-date=April 14, 2018 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180413131542/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/disneys-live-action-mulan-lands-gong-li-jet-li-1101994 |archive-date=April 13, 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Jet Li]] as [[List of Disney's Mulan characters#The Emperor of China|The Emperor]] of China, a wise benevolent ruler of China who orders the mobilization of troops via the conscription of one man from each household to fight the Hun army.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/erikkain/2019/07/07/there-are-no-talking-dragons-or-singing-generals-in-this-live-action-mulan-trailer/#1f5fae1f5f0f |title=There Are No Talking Dragons Or Singing Generals In This Live-Action 'Mulan' Trailer |last=Kain, Erik |date=July 7, 2019 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190713050758/https://www.forbes.com/sites/erikkain/2019/07/07/there-are-no-talking-dragons-or-singing-generals-in-this-live-action-mulan-trailer/#1f5fae1f5f0f |archive-date=July 13, 2019 |access-date=July 13, 2019 |magazine=[[Forbes]]}}</ref>\n* [[Tzi Ma]] as [[List of Disney's Mulan characters#Fa Zhou|Hua Zhou]], Mulan's father and a famed [[Veteran|war veteran]], who is now recalled to the Imperial Army despite his frail health.<ref name=\"HuffPost\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.huffpost.com/entry/ming-na-wen-voice-of-animated-mulan-responds-to-new-teaser_n_5d267d35e4b0583e482badeb |title=Ming-Na Wen, Voice Of Animated Mulan, Responds To New Teaser |last=Yam, Kimberly |date=July 10, 2019 |publisher=[[HuffPost]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190713090948/https://www.huffpost.com/entry/ming-na-wen-voice-of-animated-mulan-responds-to-new-teaser_n_5d267d35e4b0583e482badeb |archive-date=July 13, 2019 |access-date=July 13, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Rosalind Chao]] as [[List of Disney's Mulan characters#Fa Li|Hua Li]], Mulan's mother and Zhou's wife.<ref name=HuffPost/>\n* Xana Tang as Hua Xiu, Mulan's younger sister.<ref name=HollywoodReporter3/> The character was added to the film's plot because the filmmakers felt that \"this added a broader emotional context and added more motivation for [Mulan's] character\".<ref name=\"MulanOnSet\"/>\n* [[Ron Yuan]] as Sergeant Qiang, the fiercely loyal second in command of the Imperial Regiment.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/05/mulan-utkarsh-ambudkar-ron-yuan-disney-1202396832/ |title='Mulan': Utkarsh Ambudkar & Ron Yuan Added To Disney's Live-Action Adaptation |last=N'Duka, Amanda |date=May 23, 2018 |publisher=Deadline |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190711104710/https://deadline.com/2018/05/mulan-utkarsh-ambudkar-ron-yuan-disney-1202396832/ |archive-date=July 11, 2019 |access-date=July 13, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Jimmy Wong]] as [[List of Disney's Mulan characters#Ling|Ling]], a recruit who joins Commander Tung's unit.<ref name=\"Deadline4\">{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/08/disney-mulan-jimmy-wong-doua-moua-1202445269/ |title=Disney's 'Mulan' Casts Jimmy Wong & Doua Moua |last=N'Duka |first=Amanda |date=August 14, 2018 |publisher=Deadline |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180814232736/https://deadline.com/2018/08/disney-mulan-jimmy-wong-doua-moua-1202445269/ |archive-date=August 14, 2018 |access-date=August 14, 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Doua Moua]] as [[List of Disney's Mulan characters#Chien-Po|Chien-Po]], a recruit who joins Commander Tung's unit.<ref name=Deadline4/>\n* [[Chen Tang (actor)|Chen Tang]] as [[List of Disney's Mulan characters#Yao|Yao]], a recruit who joins Commander Tung's unit.<ref name=\"Deadline5\">{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/09/adrian-martinez-disney-lady-and-the-tramp-mulan-chen-tang-1202469095/ |title=Adrian Martinez Joins Disney's 'Lady and the Tramp'; 'Mulan' Adds Chen Tang |last=N'Duka |first=Amanda |date=September 21, 2018 |publisher=Deadline |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180921230311/https://deadline.com/2018/09/adrian-martinez-disney-lady-and-the-tramp-mulan-chen-tang-1202469095/ |archive-date=September 21, 2018 |access-date=September 21, 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Nelson Lee]] as [[List of Disney's Mulan characters#Chi-Fu|The Chancellor]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://movieweb.com/mulan-2020-disney-remake-trailer-release-date/ |title=Disney's Mulan Remake Trailer Drops This Sunday |last=Sprague, Mike |date=July 6, 2019 |publisher=MovieWeb |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190708141758/https://movieweb.com/mulan-2020-disney-remake-trailer-release-date/ |archive-date=July 8, 2019 |access-date=July 13, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Cheng Pei-pei]]<ref name=Deadline3/> as [[List of Disney's Mulan characters|The Matchmaker]] \n* [[Utkarsh Ambudkar]] as Skatch, a con artist and friend of Ramtish.<ref name=HollywoodReporter2/>\n* Chum Ehelepola as Ramtish, a con artist and friend of Skatch.<ref name=HollywoodReporter2/>\n* Arka Das as Red Fez\n* Jun Yu as Cricket, an archer.<ref name=\"Liptak\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.theverge.com/2019/7/7/20685171/mulan-live-action-yifei-liu-niki-caro-animation-remake-first-trailer-watch |title=Watch the first trailer for Disney's live-action remake of Mulan |last=Liptak |first=Andrew |date=July 7, 2019 |website=[[The Verge]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190707165408/https://www.theverge.com/2019/7/7/20685171/mulan-live-action-yifei-liu-niki-caro-animation-remake-first-trailer-watch |archive-date=July 7, 2019 |access-date=July 7, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"MulanOnSet\">{{cite web|url=https://collider.com/mulan-changes-live-action-animated-version-disney/|title=\u2018Mulan\u2019: The Biggest Changes from the Animated Version in Disney\u2019s Live-Action Remake|website=Collider|last=Szany|first=Wendy Lee|date=February 27, 2020|accessdate=February 27, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Production==\n===Development===\n[[Walt Disney Pictures]] expressed interest in a [[List of Disney live-action remakes of animated films|live-action adaptation]] of the 1998 animated film ''[[Mulan (1998 film)|Mulan]]'' starring international star [[Zhang Ziyi]], with [[Chuck Russell]] chosen as the director. The film was originally planned to start filming in October 2010, but was canceled.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.channelnewsasia.com/stories/entertainment/view/1071985/1/.html |title=Zhang Ziyi to produce and star in 3D Mulan film |date=July 28, 2010 |website=[[Channel NewsAsia]] |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130318082003/http://www.channelnewsasia.com/stories/entertainment/view/1071985/1/.html |archive-date=March 18, 2013}}</ref> On March 30, 2015, ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' reported that Disney had restarted development of the live-action adaptation with [[Chris Bender (film producer)|Chris Bender]] and [[J. C. Spink]] producing, while Elizabeth Martin and Lauren Hynek would be writing the screenplay.<ref name=\"DevelopingMulan\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/disney-developing-live-action-mulan-784892/ |title=Disney Developing Live-Action 'Mulan' (Exclusive) |last=Ford |first=Rebecca |date=March 30, 2015 |website=The Hollywood Reporter |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150403121534/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/disney-developing-live-action-mulan-784892 |archive-date=April 3, 2015 |access-date=April 5, 2015}}</ref> On October 4, 2016, it was announced that [[Rick Jaffa and Amanda Silver]] would rewrite the script, combining the Chinese ballad and the 1998 animated film, while Jason T. Reed would be producing the film along with [[Chris Bender (film producer)|Chris Bender]] and Jake Weiner.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://variety.com/2016/film/news/mulan-release-date-live-action-disney-1201877832/ |title=Disney's Live-Action 'Mulan' to Hit Theaters in November 2018; Rick Jaffa and Amanda Silver Rewriting |last=Kroll |first=Justin |date=October 4, 2016 |work=Variety |access-date=October 5, 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161005192448/http://variety.com/2016/film/news/mulan-release-date-live-action-disney-1201877832/ |archive-date=October 5, 2016}}</ref> In February 27, 2020, Reed revealed that Mulan's sidekick from the original film, [[Mushu]], was removed due to the character's negative reception in China.<ref name=\"MulanOnSet\"/> Redd also said, aside from both the original ballad and the animated film, the filmmakers drew inspiration from different Chinese adaptations of the ballad while writing the film, stating that, since \"[t]he traditional Disney audience and the diaspora Asian audience viewed the movie in one way, and the traditional Chinese in China audience viewed a slightly different way\", the filmmakers \"dug in to try and make sure that [they are] addressing both of those audiences in a thoughtful way\".<ref name=\"MulanOnSet\"/>\n\n===Casting===\n[[File:Liu Yifei at the 2016 BAZAAR Stars\u2019 Charity Night.jpg|thumb|upright|Liu Yifei plays Mulan in the remake.]]\nSince several recent Hollywood films were accused of [[Whitewashing in film|whitewashing]], ''Mulan'' has been under intense scrutiny since ''The Hollywood Reporter'' reported that Disney was making a live-action adaptation of ''[[Mulan (1998 film)|Mulan]]''. An [[online petition]] titled \"Tell Disney You Don't Want A Whitewashed Mulan!\" received more than 100,000 signatures.<ref name=BBC/> On October 4, 2016, Disney announced that a global search for a Chinese actress to portray the title role was underway.<ref name=\"FindingMulan\">{{Cite news|last=McClintock |first=Pamela |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/disneys-live-action-mulan-gets-934976 |title=Disney's Live-Action 'Mulan' Gets Winter 2018 Release Date |date=October 4, 2016 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180618014152/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/disneys-live-action-mulan-gets-934976 |archive-date=June 18, 2018 |access-date=June 22, 2018}}</ref> A team of casting directors visited five continents and saw nearly 1,000 candidates for the role with criteria that required credible martial arts skills, the ability to speak clear English, and star quality.<ref name=\"YifeiCast\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/disneys-mulan-finds-star-1061585 |title=Disney's 'Mulan' Finds Its Star (Exclusive) |last=Sun |first=Rebecca |date=November 29, 2017 |work=The Hollywood Reporter |access-date=January 17, 2018 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201044128/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/disneys-mulan-finds-star-1061585?utm_source=twitter |archive-date=December 1, 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn November 29, 2017, Chinese-American actress [[Liu Yifei]] was cast in the film to portray the titular role of Mulan. Many celebrated this as a win for diversity in Disney films.<ref name=BBC/> Further cast announcements for [[Donnie Yen]], [[Gong Li]], [[Jet Li]], and Xana Tang were made in April 2018,<ref name=Deadline1/><ref name=HollywoodReporter3/> [[Utkarsh Ambudkar]] and [[Ron Yuan]] in May,<ref name=\"AmbudkarYuanCast\">{{Cite news |url=https://deadline.com/2018/05/mulan-utkarsh-ambudkar-ron-yuan-disney-1202396832/ |title='Mulan': Utkarsh Ambudkar & Ron Yuan Added To Disney's Live-Action Adaptation |last=N'Duka |first=Amanda |date=May 23, 2018 |work=Deadline |access-date=May 24, 2018 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180524151432/http://deadline.com/2018/05/mulan-utkarsh-ambudkar-ron-yuan-disney-1202396832/ |archive-date=May 24, 2018}}</ref> [[Yoson An]] and Chum Ehelepola in June,<ref name=HollywoodReporter2/> [[Jason Scott Lee]] in July,<ref name=HollywoodReporter1/> [[Tzi Ma]], [[Rosalind Chao]], [[Cheng Pei-Pei]], [[Nelson Lee]], [[Jimmy Wong]] and [[Doua Moua]] in August,<ref name=\"Deadline3\">{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/08/mulan-production-starting-new-cast-disney-1202444587/ |title='Mulan' Rounds Out Cast, Reveals First-Look Photo As Filming Underway On Live-Action Movie |last=Hipes |first=Patrick |date=August 13, 2018 |publisher=Deadline |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180813184830/https://deadline.com/2018/08/mulan-production-starting-new-cast-disney-1202444587/ |archive-date=August 13, 2018 |access-date=August 13, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Deadline4\"/> and [[Chen Tang (actor)|Chen Tang]] in September.<ref name=Deadline5/>\n\n===Director===\nDisney originally sought an Asian director. Disney first considered [[Ang Lee]], Taiwanese film director and two-time [[Academy Award]] winner for [[Academy Award for Best Director|Best Director]]. ''The Hollywood Reporter'' mentioned that Lee was approached but declined on October 12, 2016.<ref name=\"LeePass\">{{Cite news|last=Ford|first=Rebecca|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/mulan-mania-disney-sony-hunt-937274 |title='Mulan' Mania: Disney, Sony Hunt for Asian Directors to Helm Rival Action Pics |date=October 12, 2016 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180814001804/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/mulan-mania-disney-sony-hunt-937274 |archive-date=August 14, 2018 |access-date=June 22, 2018}}</ref> According to the report, published on November 22, 2016, he said that he would like to see an Asian director leading the film, but he himself had to decline because he was still obliged to promote his film ''[[Billy Lynn's Long Halftime Walk (film)|Billy Lynn's Long Halftime Walk]]''.<ref name=\"LeeSaid\">{{Cite news |last=Lee |first=Ashley |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/rambling-reporter/ang-lee-disneys-live-action-mulan-itd-be-great-see-an-asian-director-949162 |title=Ang Lee on Disney's Live-Action 'Mulan': \"It'd Be Great to See an Asian\" Director |date=November 22, 2016 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180814001739/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/rambling-reporter/ang-lee-disneys-live-action-mulan-itd-be-great-see-an-asian-director-949162 |archive-date=August 14, 2018 |access-date=June 22, 2018}}</ref> Next, Disney met with [[Jiang Wen]] for the position; finally on February 14, 2017, [[Niki Caro]] was hired as the director of the film, which made ''Mulan'' the second Disney film with a female director and a budget above $100 million following ''[[A Wrinkle in Time (2018 film)|A Wrinkle in Time]]''.<ref name=\"NikiHelm\">{{Cite news |last=Sun |first=Rebecca |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/disneys-live-action-mulan-finds-director-975869 |title=Disney's Live-Action 'Mulan' Finds Director (Exclusive) |work=The Hollywood Reporter |access-date=February 16, 2017 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170216072040/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/disneys-live-action-mulan-finds-director-975869 |archive-date=February 16, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Filming===\n[[Principal photography]] began on August 13, 2018, at different locations in New Zealand and China and [[Wrap (filmmaking)|wrapped]] on November 25, 2018.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://omegaunderground.com/2018/04/12/update-disney-to-begin-shooting-mulan-this-august-in-new-zealand-and-china/ |title=UPDATE: Disney To Begin Shooting 'Mulan' This August In New Zealand and China - Omega Underground |last=Marc |first=Christopher |date=April 12, 2018 |work=omegaunderground.com |access-date=April 12, 2018 |archive-date=August 16, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180816062124/https://thegww.com/update-disney-to-begin-shooting-mulan-this-august-in-new-zealand-and-china/}}</ref><ref name=Deadline3/> According to actress [[Gong Li]], the film's production budget was $290\u2013300 million due to the \"massive and...unprecedented scale\" of the sets,<ref name=\"GongLiBudget\">{{Cite web |url=https://heroichollywood.com/mulan-disney-li-gong-budget/ |title=Gong Li Claims Live-Action 'Mulan' Budget Is More Than $300 Million |last=Caesar Galvin |date=May 19, 2019 |website=Heroic Hollywood |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190718220408/https://heroichollywood.com/mulan-disney-li-gong-budget/ |archive-date=July 18, 2019 |access-date=July 19, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"GongLiBudget2\">{{Cite web |last=Bonomolo |first=Cameron |url=https://comicbook.com/movies/2018/05/07/disney-live-action-mulan-budget-most-expensive-movies-ever-made/ |title=Disney's Live-Action 'Mulan' Budget Makes It One of the Most Expensive Movies Ever Made |date=May 8, 2019 |website=ComicBook.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190718183231/https://comicbook.com/movies/2018/05/07/disney-live-action-mulan-budget-most-expensive-movies-ever-made/ |archive-date=July 18, 2019 |access-date=July 19, 2019}}</ref> although the actual figure was later reported to be $200 million.<ref name=CNNbudget/><ref>{{cite news|last=Ford|first=Rebecca|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/features/inside-disneys-bold-200m-gamble-mulan-stakes-couldnt-be-higher-1280999|title=Inside Disney's Bold $200M Gamble on 'Mulan': \"The Stakes Couldn't Be Higher\"|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=February 26, 2020|access-date=February 26, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Post-production===\nThe visual effects are provided by [[Sony Pictures Imageworks]], [[Weta Digital]], [[Framestore]], and [[Image Engine]], with Seth Maury and [[Anders Langlands|Andres Langlands]] serving as visual effects supervisors and [[Sean Andrew Faden]] serving as production supervisor.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.artofvfx.com/mulan/ |title=Mulan - ART OF VFX |date=July 8, 2019 |website=www.artofvfx.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190708122921/https://www.artofvfx.com/mulan/ |archive-date=July 8, 2019 |access-date=July 8, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Music===\nDirector [[Niki Caro]] revealed that the remake won't feature any songs from the original film;<ref>{{Cite web |last=Taylor |first=Drew |url=https://www.moviefone.com/2017/03/17/mulan-exclusive-niki-caro/ |title=Exclusive: 'Mulan' Director Niki Caro Says No Songs in the Upcoming Remake |date=March 17, 2018 |website=MovieFone |url-status=live |access-date=January 13, 2020}}</ref> the film instead will feature instrumental versions of the original film's songs.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Colon |first=Jessenika |url=https://thedisinsider.com/2019/06/29/exclusive-phoenix-possibly-replacing-mushu-in-mulan-cast-will-not-sing-classic-songs/ |title=EXCLUSIVE: Phoenix Possibly Replacing Mushu in 'Mulan'; Cast Will Not Sing Classic Songs |date=June 30, 2019|website=www.thedisinsider.com |url-status=live |access-date=January 13, 2020}}</ref> Caro later explained that the songs were deleted because she felt it didn't fit with her realistic vision of the film; she believes that since people do not break out into song as they enter war, the film should not either. Though she still tried to \"honour the music from the animation in a very significant way\",<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/benhenry/mulan-director-niki-caro-q-and-a|title=The Director Of \"Mulan\" Just Revealed Why There Won't Be Any Songs In Disney's Live-Action Remake|date=January 13, 2020|website=BuzzFeed|url-status=live|access-date=January 13, 2020}}</ref> she did not want to disrespect the original film in any way; however, she claimed she could not find a place to squeeze in the original music. Producer Jason T. Reed clarified Caro's previous statement by saying that the songs will be featured \"in a slightly different way\" in the remake.<ref name=\"MulanOnSet\"/>\n\n[[Harry Gregson-Williams]], who previously worked with Caro on ''[[The Zookeeper's Wife (film)|The Zookeeper's Wife]]'', composed the film's score.<ref name=\"Gregson-Williams\"/>\n\n[[Matthew Wilder]], who previously co-wrote the songs for the original film, revealed that the remake will feature a new version of the song \"[[Reflection (song)|Reflection]]\", and that the song \"thematically plays a large part in the new movie throughout the score\".<ref>{{Cite web |last=Shuler |first=Skyler |url=https://thedisinsider.com/2020/02/13/matthew-wilder-reflection-mulan/ |title=Songwriter Matthew Wilder Discusses \"Reflection\" In Disney\u2019s \u2018Mulan\u2019 |date=February 13, 2020|website=www.thedisinsider.com |url-status=live |access-date=February 27, 2020}}</ref> [[Christina Aguilera]], who previously performed an end-credits version of \"Reflection\" for the original film, confirmed during a performance in [[The Xperience]] that she had recorded a new version of \"Reflection\", as well as new material for the remake's soundtrack.<ref>{{cite news |last=Lenker |first=Maureen Lee |url=https://ew.com/movies/christina-aguilera-new-mulan-music/ |title=Original 'Reflection' singer Christina Aguilera has recorded new material for live-action Mulan |work=Entertainment Weekly |date=February 27, 2020 |accessdate=March 4, 2020}}</ref> On March 6, 2020, she released a new single for the film's soundtrack, titled \"Loyal Brave True\". The song was written by Jamie Hartman, Harry Gregson-Williams, Rosi Golan and Billy Crabtree, and produced by Jamie Hartman. The song was also released in Spanish, as \u201cEl Mejor Guerrero.\u201d Additionally, the singer confirmed that she would also release a re-recorded version of \"Reflection\".\n<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.thedigitalfix.com/music/new-music/christina-aguilera-shares-her-track-loyal-brave-true-taken-from-the-upcoming-disney-remake-of-mulan/ |title=Christina Aguilera shares her track, 'Loyal Brave True', taken from the upcoming Disney remake of Mulan|website=The Digital Fix |date=March 6, 2020}}</ref>\n<ref>{{cite news|first=Joey|last=Nolfi|url=https://ew.com/movies/christina-aguilera-new-song-loyal-brave-true-mulan/|title=Hear Christina Aguilera's warrior spirit on new Mulan ballad 'Loyal Brave True'|work=Entertainment Weekly|date=March 6, 2020|accessdate=March 6, 2020}}</ref> On March 8, a [[Mandarin Chinese|Mandarin]]-version of the song performed by Liu Yifei was released.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.chinadaily.com.cn/a/202003/09/WS5e65cb3ca31012821727d709.html|title=Chinese version of 'Reflection' released for upcoming 'Mulan' - Chinadaily.com.cn|last=\u987e\u99a8|website=www.chinadaily.com.cn|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref> Liu's interpretation is a revisitation of the Mandarin-language version of Aguilera's song, originally performed for the animated movie by [[Hong Kong]]-[[Chinese Americans|Chinese American]] singer [[Coco Lee]], who also voiced Mulan in the [[Taiwanese Mandarin]] dubbing in 1998.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=f7Z6FhaAPFI|title=\u674e\u739f CoCo Lee - \u81ea\u5df1|last=|first=|date=|website=YouTube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://disneyinternationalvoices.weebly.com/mulan.html|title=Mulan|website=CHARGUIGOU|language=fr|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref>\n\n==Marketing==\nOn July 7, 2019, the official teaser trailer and the official teaser poster were released during the broadcast of the [[2019 FIFA Women's World Cup Final]].<ref name=\"Liptak\"/> The teaser trailer was viewed 175.1 million times in its first 24 hours, including 52 million from China, making it [[List of most-viewed online videos in the first 24 hours#Top trailers|the seventh most viewed trailer in that time period]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/07/mulan-teaser-trailer-175-million-views-24-hours-china-worldwide-disney-1202643480/ |title='Mulan' Teaser Trailer Logs Epic 175M+ Views In First 24 Hours, Including 52M From China |last=Tartaglione |first=Nancy |date=July 9, 2019 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190827031552/https://deadline.com/2019/07/mulan-teaser-trailer-175-million-views-24-hours-china-worldwide-disney-1202643480/ |archive-date=August 27, 2019 |access-date=December 6, 2019}}</ref> On September 30, an exclusive photo featuring Liu as a soldier in the Imperial Army was released on Empire's upcoming ''[[Star Wars: The Rise of Skywalker]]'' issue.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.empireonline.com/movies/news/mulan-disney-remake-david-lean-akira-kurosawa/ |title=Mulan Live-Action Remake Taking 'David Lean Or Kurosawa Approach'- Exclusive Image |last=Travis |first=Ben |date=September 30, 2019 |website=[[Empire (magazine)|Empire]] |access-date=September 30, 2019}}</ref> On October 24, a prequel novel written by writer [[Grace Lin]] was announced along with a preview being made available online. Entitled ''Mulan: Before the Sword'', the novel was announced to be released on February 11, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://ew.com/books/2019/10/24/grace-lin-mulan-novel-cover-excerpt/ |title=Exclusive preview: Grace Lin fashions a gorgeous original Mulan novel |last=Canfield |first=David |date=October 29, 2019 |website=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |access-date=February 17, 2020}}</ref> On November 4, a video clip filmed during a Toho cinema preview was leaked online, featuring new shots of Mulan as a warrior battling fiercely and taking off her hair band.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://tieba.baidu.com/p/6324507746/ |title=New shots and new lines from Mulan |date=November 4, 2019 |website=[[Baidu]] |access-date=November 4, 2019}}</ref> On November 6, Liu was featured as one of the 25 stars of Next Gen Talent 2019 nominated by ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' with two new studio stills released concurrently.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/next-gen-talent-2019-hollywoods-rising-young-stars-revealed-1250276/ |title=Next Gen Talent 2019: Hollywood's Rising Young Stars Revealed |last=Elise Sandberg |first=Bryn |date=November 6, 2019 |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |access-date=November 6, 2019}}</ref> On November 20, the Japanese theatrical poster was released online.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.reddit.com/r/movies/comments/dz0cjv/japanese_poster_of_disneys_liveaction_movie_mulan/ |title=Japanese Poster of Disney's live-action movie Mulan |date=November 20, 2019 |website=[[Reddit]] |access-date=November 20, 2019}}</ref> On December 5, the official trailer was released with dual versions: the Chinese Weibo debuted a shorter version with different cut and a few shots that were not featured in the US version.{{citation needed|date=January 2020}} On January 26, 2020, 6 individual character posters were released.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://collider.com/mulan-character-posters-liu-yifei-donnie-yen/#mulan-character-poster-liu-yifei|title=These New 'Mulan' Character Posters Will Make a Fan Out of You|first=Allie|last=Gemmill|work=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]|date=January 26, 2020|accessdate=February 23, 2020}}</ref> On February 2, 2020, the final trailer was released.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thewrap.com/mulan-final-trailer-puts-villains-in-the-spotlight-video/|title=\u2018Mulan': Final Trailer Puts Villains in the Spotlight (Video)|first=Jeremy|last=Fuster|work=[[The Wrap]]|date=March 10, 2020|accessdate=February 2, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Release==\n''Mulan'' had its world premiere at the [[Dolby Theatre]] in Hollywood on March 9, 2020.<ref>{{Cite news |url= https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/mulan-first-reactions-premiere-1283199 |title= 'Mulan': First Reactions from the Premiere |date=March 9, 2020 |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |access-date=March 10, 2020}}</ref> It had been originally set for a November 2, 2018, release but was delayed, with ''[[The Nutcracker and the Four Realms]]'' taking its slot.<ref name=\"FindingMulan\" /> It was then scheduled to be released in the United States on March 27, 2020,<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/mulan-reboot-release-date-pushed-back-1202714825/ |title='Mulan' Live-Action Reboot Pushed Back to 2020 |last=Khatchatourian |first=Maane |date=March 1, 2018 |work=Variety |access-date=March 1, 2018 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180302162410/http://variety.com/2018/film/news/mulan-reboot-release-date-pushed-back-1202714825/ |archive-date=March 2, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"NewRelease\">{{Cite news |last1=McClintock |first1=Pamela |last2=Couch |first2=Aaron |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/live-action-mulan-pushed-back-more-a-year-spring-2020-1090015 |title=Live-Action 'Mulan' Pushed Back More Than a Year to Spring 2020 |date=March 1, 2018 |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180616053315/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/live-action-mulan-pushed-back-more-a-year-spring-2020-1090015 |archive-date=June 16, 2018 |access-date=June 21, 2018}}</ref> but was delayed again due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/mulan-release-pushed-back-coronavirus-pandemic-1284275|title='Mulan' Release Pushed Back Amid Coronavirus Pandemic|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|first=Mia|last=Galuppo|date=March 12, 2020|accessdate=March 12, 2020}}</ref> The film is scheduled to be released on July 24, 2020, taking the former slot of ''[[Jungle Cruise (film)|Jungle Cruise]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/black-widow-mulan-nab-new-release-dates-jungle-cruise-delayed-a-year-1286854|title='Black Widow,' 'Mulan' Land New 2020 Release Dates, 'Jungle Cruise' Delayed a Year|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|first=Pamela |last=McClintock  |archive-date= April 3, 2020|access-date=April 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Controversies ==\nA call to boycott the film began when Liu Yifei reshared an image posted by Chinese newspaper ''[[People's Daily]]''. The image included a quote from Chinese reporter [[List of August 2019 Hong Kong protests#12\u201314 August police brutality protests|Fu Guohao]] who worked for the ''[[Global Times]]'' and was subsequently assaulted by protesters during the [[2019 Hong Kong anti-extradition bill protests]]: \"I support Hong Kong police. You can beat me now. What a shame for Hong Kong.\" This sparked international controversy, with Liu being accused of supporting [[police brutality]]. The hashtag, #BoycottMulan, has since started trending supporting a boycott of the movie.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Ramzy |first=Austin |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/08/14/world/asia/hong-kong-airport-protests.html |title=Soul Searching Among Hong Kong Protesters After Chaos at Airport |date=August 14, 2019 |work=[[The New York Times]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190818034516/https://www.nytimes.com/2019/08/14/world/asia/hong-kong-airport-protests.html |archive-date=August 18, 2019 |access-date=August 16, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Yeung |first=Jessie |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2019/08/16/asia/china-mulan-actor-protests-intl-hnk-trnd/index.html |title=Hong Kong protesters call for 'Mulan' boycott after star went public in support of police |date=August 16, 2019 |website=[[CNN]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190818081756/https://edition.cnn.com/2019/08/16/asia/china-mulan-actor-protests-intl-hnk-trnd/index.html |archive-date=August 18, 2019 |access-date=August 16, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-49373276 |title=Liu Yifei: Mulan boycott urged after star backs HK police |date=August 16, 2019 |website=[[BBC]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190818003707/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-49373276 |archive-date=August 18, 2019 |access-date=August 16, 2019}}</ref> In response to the controversy, Liu was not present at the 2019 [[D23 Expo]], which gave fans an exclusive sneak peek of the film.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/mulan-cast-d23-boycottmulan-1203311115/ |title='Mulan' Star Crystal Yifei Liu Skips D23 Amid International Controversy |last=Nissen |first=Dano |date=August 24, 2019 |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |access-date=October 26, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn February 27, 2020, film producer Jason T. Reed said that Mulan's love interest [[List of Disney's Mulan characters#Li Shang|Captain Li Shang]] was dropped in response to the [[Me Too movement]]. In his statement, he explained that \"having a commanding officer that is also the sexual love interest was very uncomfortable and we didn\u2019t think it was appropriate\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://collider.com/mulan-li-shang-not-in-live-action-remake-reason-why/|title='Mulan': Why Captain Li Shang Isn't in the Live-Action Remake|last=Szany|first=Wendy Lee|work=Collider|date=February 27, 2020|access-date=March 2, 2020}}</ref> The reasoning behind the removal was met with social media backlash from fans of the original film and members of the [[LGBTQ]] community, who deemed Shang's relationship with Mulan's male [[alter ego]] Ping to be [[bisexual]].<ref name=\"Forbes\">{{cite news|last=Maleh|first=Linda|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/lindamaleh/2020/02/28/disney-blames-metoo-for-li-shangs-absence-from-mulan-in-new-controversy/#2c41d8e95965|title=Disney Blames #MeToo For Li Shang's Absence From 'Mulan' In New Controversy|work=Forbes|date=February 28, 2020|accessdate=March 2, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-51707188|title=Mulan: Disney drop character following #MeToo movement|publisher=BBC News|date=March 2, 2020|accessdate=March 2, 2020}}</ref> Reed was initially surprised by criticism of Shang's removal, but acknowledged that the character had become a \"LGBTQ icon\",<ref name=\"Vogue\">{{cite news|last=Rearick|first=Lauren|url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/mulan-love-interest-li-shang-reportedly-split-two-characters-metoo|title=Mulan\" Love Interest Li Shang Was Reportedly Split Into Two Characters Because of MeToo|work=Teen Vogue|date=February 28, 2020|accessdate=March 2, 2020}}</ref> and clarified that Shang's role would be served by two new characters, Commander Tung and Chen Honghui.<ref name=\"Forbes\"/><ref name=\"Vogue\"/>\n\n==Sequel==\nIn April 2020, it was announced that a ''Mulan'' sequel is in development at Disney with Chris Bender, Jason T. Reed and Jake Weiner returning as producers for sequel.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://fullcirclecinema.com/2020/04/18/mulan-2-early-development-disney/|title=\u2018Mulan 2\u2019 Reportedly In Early Development At Disney|magazine=Full Circle Cinema|last=Campbell|first=Jacob|date=April 18, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|https://movies.disney.com/mulan-2020}}\n* {{IMDb title|4566758}}\n\n{{Disney's Mulan}}\n{{Disney Princess}}\n{{Disney's live-action adaptations of animated franchises}}\n{{Niki Caro}}\n{{Rick Jaffa and Amanda Silver}}\n\n[[Category:2020 3D films]]\n[[Category:2020s action drama films]]\n[[Category:2020s fantasy films]]\n[[Category:2020s feminist films]]\n[[Category:American 3D films]]\n[[Category:American action adventure films]]\n[[Category:American action films]]\n[[Category:American adventure films]]\n[[Category:American fantasy adventure films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American martial arts films]]\n[[Category:American war films]]\n[[Category:Cross-dressing in American films]]\n[[Category:Disney film remakes]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Film remakes]]\n[[Category:Films about sexism]]\n[[Category:Films about witchcraft]]\n[[Category:Films based on adaptations]]\n[[Category:Films based on multiple works]]\n[[Category:Films dir